V8 is Googleâ€™s open source high-performance JavaScript and WebAssembly engine, written in C++. It is used in Chrome and in Node.js, among others. It implements ECMAScript and WebAssembly, and runs on Windows, macOS, and Linux systems that use x64, IA-32, or ARM processors. V8 can be embedded into any C++ application.

69 Do_not_use_kScratchDoubleRegister_in_arch_independent_code {

89void NodeBase::CheckCanOverwriteWith(Opcode new_opcode,
90 OpProperties new_properties) {
91 if (new_opcode == Opcode::kDead) return;
92
93 DCHECK_IMPLIES(new_properties.can_eager_deopt(),
94 properties().can_eager_deopt());
95 DCHECK_IMPLIES(new_properties.can_lazy_deopt(),
96 properties().can_lazy_deopt());
97 DCHECK_IMPLIES(new_properties.needs_register_snapshot(),
98 properties().needs_register_snapshot());
99
100 int old_input_count = input_count();
101 size_t old_sizeof = -1;
102 switch (opcode()) {
103#define CASE(op) \
104 case Opcode::k##op: \
105 old_sizeof = sizeof(op); \
106 break;
107 NODE_BASE_LIST(CASE);
108#undef CASE
109 }
110
111 switch (new_opcode) {
112#define CASE(op) \
113 case Opcode::k##op: { \
114 DCHECK_EQ(old_input_count, StaticInputCount(static_cast<op*>(this))); \
115 DCHECK_EQ(sizeof(op), old_sizeof); \
116 break; \
117 }
118 NODE_BASE_LIST(CASE)
119#undef CASE
120 }
121}

125bool Phi::is_loop_phi() const { return merge_state()->is_loop(); }

128 DCHECK(is_loop_phi());
129 return merge_state()->is_unmerged_loop();

131
132void Phi::RecordUseReprHint(UseRepresentationSet repr_mask,
133 int current_offset) {
134 if (is_loop_phi() && merge_state()->HasLoopInfo() &&
135 merge_state()->loop_info()->Contains(current_offset)) {
136 same_loop_uses_repr_hint_.Add(repr_mask);
137 }
138
139 if (!repr_mask.is_subset_of(uses_repr_hint_)) {
140 uses_repr_hint_.Add(repr_mask);
141
142 // Propagate in inputs, ignoring unbounded loop backedges.
143 int bound_inputs = input_count();
144 if (merge_state()->is_unmerged_loop()) --bound_inputs;
145
146 for (int i = 0; i < bound_inputs; i++) {
147 if (Phi* phi_input = input(i).node()->TryCast<Phi>()) {
148 phi_input->RecordUseReprHint(repr_mask, current_offset);
149 }
150 }
151 }
152}
153
154void Phi::SetUseRequires31BitValue() {
155 if (uses_require_31_bit_value()) return;
156 set_uses_require_31_bit_value();
157 auto inputs =
158 is_loop_phi() ? merge_state_->predecessors_so_far() : input_count();
159 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < inputs; ++i) {
160 ValueNode* input_node = input(i).node();
161 DCHECK(input_node);
162 if (auto phi = input_node->TryCast<Phi>()) {
163 phi->SetUseRequires31BitValue();
164 }
165 }
166}

177bool IsStoreToNonEscapedObject(const NodeBase* node) {
178 switch (node->opcode()) {
179 case Opcode::kStoreMap:
180 case Opcode::kStoreTaggedFieldWithWriteBarrier:
181 case Opcode::kStoreTaggedFieldNoWriteBarrier:
182 case Opcode::kStoreScriptContextSlotWithWriteBarrier:
183 case Opcode::kStoreFloat64:
184 DCHECK_GT(node->input_count(), 0);
185 if (InlinedAllocation* alloc =
186 node->input(0).node()->template TryCast<InlinedAllocation>()) {
187 return alloc->HasBeenAnalysed() && alloc->HasBeenElided();
188 }
189 return false;
190 default:
191 return false;
192 }
193}

195void PrintInputs(std::ostream& os, MaglevGraphLabeller* graph_labeller,
196 const NodeBase* node) {
197 if (!node->has_inputs()) return;
198
199 os << " [";
200 for (int i = 0; i < node->input_count(); i++) {
201 if (i != 0) os << ", ";
202 graph_labeller->PrintInput(os, node->input(i));
203 }
204 if (IsStoreToNonEscapedObject(node)) {
205 os << " ðŸª¦";
206 }
207 os << "]";
208}

210void PrintResult(std::ostream& os, MaglevGraphLabeller* graph_labeller,
211 const NodeBase* node) {}
212
213void PrintResult(std::ostream& os, MaglevGraphLabeller* graph_labeller,
214 const ValueNode* node) {
215 os << " â†’ " << node->result().operand();
216 if (node->result().operand().IsAllocated() && node->is_spilled() &&
217 node->spill_slot() != node->result().operand()) {
218 os << " (spilled: " << node->spill_slot() << ")";
219 }
220 if (node->has_valid_live_range()) {
221 os << ", live range: [" << node->live_range().start << "-"
222 << node->live_range().end << "]";
223 }
224 if (!node->has_id()) {
225 os << ", " << node->use_count() << " uses";
226 if (const InlinedAllocation* alloc = node->TryCast<InlinedAllocation>()) {
227 os << " (" << alloc->non_escaping_use_count() << " non escaping uses)";
228 if (alloc->HasBeenAnalysed() && alloc->HasBeenElided()) {
229 os << " ðŸª¦";
230 }
231 } else if (!node->is_used()) {
232 if (node->opcode() != Opcode::kAllocationBlock &&
233 node->properties().is_required_when_unused()) {
234 os << ", but required";
235 } else {
236 os << " ðŸª¦";
237 }
238 }
239 }
240}

256void PrintTargets(std::ostream& os, MaglevGraphLabeller* graph_labeller,
257 const Switch* node) {
258 for (int i = 0; i < node->size(); i++) {
259 const BasicBlockRef& target = node->Cast<Switch>()->targets()[i];
260 os << " b" << graph_labeller->BlockId(target.block_ptr());
261 }
262 if (node->Cast<Switch>()->has_fallthrough()) {
263 BasicBlock* fallthrough_target = node->Cast<Switch>()->fallthrough();
264 os << " b" << graph_labeller->BlockId(fallthrough_target);
265 }

268class MaybeUnparkForPrint {
269 public:
270 MaybeUnparkForPrint() {
271 LocalHeap* local_heap = LocalHeap::Current();
272 if (!local_heap) {
273 local_heap = Isolate::Current()->main_thread_local_heap();
274 }
275 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(local_heap);
276 if (local_heap->IsParked()) {
277 scope_.emplace(local_heap);
278 }
279 }
280
281 private:
282 std::optional<UnparkedScope> scope_;
283};
284
285template <typename NodeT>
286void PrintImpl(std::ostream& os, MaglevGraphLabeller* graph_labeller,
287 const NodeT* node, bool skip_targets) {
288 MaybeUnparkForPrint unpark;
289 os << node->opcode();
290 node->PrintParams(os, graph_labeller);
291 PrintInputs(os, graph_labeller, node);
292 PrintResult(os, graph_labeller, node);
293 if (!skip_targets) {
294 PrintTargets(os, graph_labeller, node);
295 }
296}

298bool RootToBoolean(RootIndex index) {
299 switch (index) {
300 case RootIndex::kFalseValue:
301 case RootIndex::kNullValue:
302 case RootIndex::kUndefinedValue:
303 case RootIndex::kNanValue:
304 case RootIndex::kHoleNanValue:
305 case RootIndex::kMinusZeroValue:
306 case RootIndex::kempty_string:
307#ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
308 case RootIndex::kWasmNull:
309#endif
310 return false;
311 default:
312 return true;
313 }
314}
315
316#ifdef DEBUG
317// For all RO roots, check that RootToBoolean returns the same value as
318// BooleanValue on that root.
319bool CheckToBooleanOnAllRoots(LocalIsolate* local_isolate) {
320 ReadOnlyRoots roots(local_isolate);
321 // Use the READ_ONLY_ROOT_LIST macro list rather than a for loop to get nicer
322 // error messages if there is a failure.
323#define DO_CHECK(type, name, CamelName) \
324 /* Ignore 'undefined' roots that are not the undefined value itself. */ \
325 if (roots.name() != roots.undefined_value() || \
326 RootIndex::k##CamelName == RootIndex::kUndefinedValue) { \
327 DCHECK_EQ(Object::BooleanValue(roots.name(), local_isolate), \
328 RootToBoolean(RootIndex::k##CamelName)); \
329 }
330 READ_ONLY_ROOT_LIST(DO_CHECK)
331#undef DO_CHECK
332 return true;
333}
334#endif

336size_t GetInputLocationSizeForValueNode(VirtualObject::List virtual_objects,
337 ValueNode* value) {
338 // We allocate the space needed for the Virtual Object plus one location
339 // used if the allocation escapes.
340 DCHECK(!value->Is<VirtualObject>());
341 if (const InlinedAllocation* alloc = value->TryCast<InlinedAllocation>()) {
342 VirtualObject* vobject = virtual_objects.FindAllocatedWith(alloc);
343 CHECK_NOT_NULL(vobject);
344 return vobject->InputLocationSizeNeeded(virtual_objects) + 1;
345 }
346 return 1;
347}
348
349size_t GetInputLocationSizeForArray(VirtualObject::List virtual_objects,
350 base::Vector<ValueNode*> array) {
351 size_t size = 0;
352 for (ValueNode* value : array) {
353 size += GetInputLocationSizeForValueNode(virtual_objects, value);
354 }
355 return size;
356}
357
358size_t GetInputLocationSizeForCompactFrame(
359 const MaglevCompilationUnit& unit, VirtualObject::List virtual_objects,
360 const CompactInterpreterFrameState* frame) {
361 size_t size = 0;
362 frame->ForEachValue(unit, [&](ValueNode* value, interpreter::Register) {
363 if (value != nullptr) {
364 size += GetInputLocationSizeForValueNode(virtual_objects, value);
365 }
366 });
367 return size;
368}
369
370size_t GetInputLocationSizeForVirtualObjectSlot(
371 VirtualObject::List virtual_objects, ValueNode* node) {
372 if (IsConstantNode(node->opcode()) ||
373 node->opcode() == Opcode::kArgumentsElements ||
374 node->opcode() == Opcode::kArgumentsLength ||
375 node->opcode() == Opcode::kRestLength) {
376 return 0;
377 }
378 return GetInputLocationSizeForValueNode(virtual_objects, node);
379}
380
381} // namespace
382
383size_t VirtualObject::InputLocationSizeNeeded(
384 VirtualObject::List virtual_objects) const {
385 if (type() != kDefault) return 0;
386 size_t size = 0;
387 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < slot_count(); i++) {
388 size += GetInputLocationSizeForVirtualObjectSlot(virtual_objects,
389 slots_.data[i]);
390 }
391 return size;
392}

394void VirtualObject::List::Print(std::ostream& os, const char* prefix,
395 MaglevGraphLabeller* labeller) const {
396 CHECK_NOT_NULL(labeller);
397 os << prefix;
398 for (const VirtualObject* vo : *this) {
399 labeller->PrintNodeLabel(os, vo);
400 os << "; ";
401 }
402 os << std::endl;
403}

405size_t DeoptFrame::GetInputLocationsArraySize() const {
406 size_t size = 0;
407 const DeoptFrame* frame = this;
408 VirtualObject::List virtual_objects = GetVirtualObjects(*frame);
409 do {
410 switch (frame->type()) {
411 case DeoptFrame::FrameType::kInterpretedFrame:
412 size += GetInputLocationSizeForValueNode(
413 virtual_objects, frame->as_interpreted().closure()) +
414 GetInputLocationSizeForCompactFrame(
415 frame->as_interpreted().unit(), virtual_objects,
416 frame->as_interpreted().frame_state());
417 break;
418 case DeoptFrame::FrameType::kInlinedArgumentsFrame:
419 size += GetInputLocationSizeForValueNode(
420 virtual_objects, frame->as_inlined_arguments().closure()) +
421 GetInputLocationSizeForArray(
422 virtual_objects, frame->as_inlined_arguments().arguments());
423 break;
424 case DeoptFrame::FrameType::kConstructInvokeStubFrame:
425 size += GetInputLocationSizeForValueNode(
426 virtual_objects, frame->as_construct_stub().receiver()) +
427 GetInputLocationSizeForValueNode(
428 virtual_objects, frame->as_construct_stub().context());
429 break;
430 case DeoptFrame::FrameType::kBuiltinContinuationFrame:
431 size +=
432 GetInputLocationSizeForArray(
433 virtual_objects,
434 frame->as_builtin_continuation().parameters()) +
435 GetInputLocationSizeForValueNode(
436 virtual_objects, frame->as_builtin_continuation().context());
437 break;
438 }
439 frame = frame->parent();
440 } while (frame != nullptr);
441 return size;
442}

444bool RootConstant::ToBoolean(LocalIsolate* local_isolate) const {
445#ifdef DEBUG
446 // (Ab)use static locals to call CheckToBooleanOnAllRoots once, on first
447 // call to this function.
448 static bool check_once = CheckToBooleanOnAllRoots(local_isolate);
449 DCHECK(check_once);
450#endif
451 // ToBoolean is only supported for RO roots.
452 DCHECK(RootsTable::IsReadOnly(index_));
453 return RootToBoolean(index_);
454}

456bool FromConstantToBool(LocalIsolate* local_isolate, ValueNode* node) {
457 DCHECK(IsConstantNode(node->opcode()));
458 switch (node->opcode()) {
459#define CASE(Name) \
460 case Opcode::k##Name: { \
461 return node->Cast<Name>()->ToBoolean(local_isolate); \
462 }
463 CONSTANT_VALUE_NODE_LIST(CASE)
464#undef CASE
465 default:
466 UNREACHABLE();
467 }
468}

475DeoptInfo::DeoptInfo(Zone* zone, const DeoptFrame top_frame,
476 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_to_update,
477 size_t input_locations_size)
478 : top_frame_(top_frame),
479 feedback_to_update_(feedback_to_update),
480 input_locations_(
481 zone->AllocateArray<InputLocation>(input_locations_size)) {
482 // Initialise InputLocations so that they correctly don't have a next use id.
483 for (size_t i = 0; i < input_locations_size; ++i) {

488#endif // DEBUG

491bool LazyDeoptInfo::IsResultRegister(interpreter::Register reg) const {
492 if (top_frame().type() == DeoptFrame::FrameType::kConstructInvokeStubFrame) {
493 return reg == interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator();
494 }
495 if (V8_LIKELY(result_size() == 1)) {
496 return reg == result_location_;
497 }
498 if (result_size() == 0) {
499 return false;
500 }
501 DCHECK_EQ(result_size(), 2);
502 return reg == result_location_ ||
503 reg == interpreter::Register(result_location_.index() + 1);
504}
505
506bool LazyDeoptInfo::InReturnValues(interpreter::Register reg,
507 interpreter::Register result_location,
508 int result_size) {
509 if (result_size == 0 || !result_location.is_valid()) {
510 return false;
511 }
512 return base::IsInRange(reg.index(), result_location.index(),
513 result_location.index() + result_size - 1);
514}
515
516int InterpretedDeoptFrame::ComputeReturnOffset(
517 interpreter::Register result_location, int result_size) const {
518 // Return offsets are counted from the end of the translation frame,
519 // which is the array [parameters..., locals..., accumulator]. Since
520 // it's the end, we don't need to worry about earlier frames.
521 if (result_location == interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator()) {
522 return 0;
523 } else if (result_location.is_parameter()) {
524 // This is slightly tricky to reason about because of zero indexing
525 // and fence post errors. As an example, consider a frame with 2
526 // locals and 2 parameters, where we want argument index 1 -- looking
527 // at the array in reverse order we have:
528 // [acc, r1, r0, a1, a0]
529 // ^
530 // and this calculation gives, correctly:
531 // 2 + 2 - 1 = 3
532 return unit().register_count() + unit().parameter_count() -
533 result_location.ToParameterIndex();
534 } else {
535 return unit().register_count() - result_location.index();
536 }
537}
538
539const InterpretedDeoptFrame& LazyDeoptInfo::GetFrameForExceptionHandler(
540 const ExceptionHandlerInfo* handler_info) {
541 const DeoptFrame* target_frame = &top_frame();
542 for (int i = 0;; i++) {
543 while (target_frame->type() != DeoptFrame::FrameType::kInterpretedFrame) {
544 target_frame = target_frame->parent();
545 }
546 if (i == handler_info->depth) break;
547 target_frame = target_frame->parent();
548 }
549 return target_frame->as_interpreted();
550}

570void ValueNode::SetHint(compiler::InstructionOperand hint) {
571 if (!hint_.IsInvalid()) return;
572 hint_ = hint;
573 if (result_.operand().IsUnallocated()) {
574 auto operand = compiler::UnallocatedOperand::cast(result_.operand());
575 if (operand.HasSameAsInputPolicy()) {
576 input(operand.input_index()).node()->SetHint(hint);
577 }
578 }
579 if (this->Is<Phi>()) {
580 for (Input& input : *this) {
581 if (input.node()->has_id() && input.node()->id() < this->id()) {
582 input.node()->SetHint(hint);
583 }
584 }
585 }
586}

603 .virtual_register());

619
620ValueRepresentation ToValueRepresentation(MachineType type) {
621 switch (type.representation()) {
622 case MachineRepresentation::kTagged:
623 case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned:
624 case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer:
625 return ValueRepresentation::kTagged;
626 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
627 return ValueRepresentation::kFloat64;
628 case MachineRepresentation::kWord64:
629 DCHECK_EQ(kSystemPointerSize, 8);
630 return ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr;
631 default:
632 return ValueRepresentation::kInt32;
633 }
634}
635
636void CheckValueInputIs(const NodeBase* node, int i,
637 ValueRepresentation expected,
638 MaglevGraphLabeller* graph_labeller) {
639 ValueNode* input = node->input(i).node();
640 DCHECK(!input->Is<Identity>());
641 ValueRepresentation got = input->properties().value_representation();
642 // Allow Float64 values to be inputs when HoleyFloat64 is expected.
643 bool valid =
644 (got == expected) || (got == ValueRepresentation::kFloat64 &&
645 expected == ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64);
646 if (!valid) {
647 std::ostringstream str;
648 str << "Type representation error: node ";
649 if (graph_labeller) {
650 str << "#" << graph_labeller->NodeId(node) << " : ";
651 }
652 str << node->opcode() << " (input @" << i << " = " << input->opcode()
653 << ") type " << got << " is not " << expected;
654 FATAL("%s", str.str().c_str());
655 }
656}
657
658void CheckValueInputIs(const NodeBase* node, int i, Opcode expected,
659 MaglevGraphLabeller* graph_labeller) {
660 ValueNode* input = node->input(i).node();
661 Opcode got = input->opcode();
662 if (got != expected) {
663 std::ostringstream str;
664 str << "Opcode error: node ";
665 if (graph_labeller) {
666 str << "#" << graph_labeller->NodeId(node) << " : ";
667 }
668 str << node->opcode() << " (input @" << i << " = " << input->opcode()
669 << ") opcode " << got << " is not " << expected;
670 FATAL("%s", str.str().c_str());
671 }
672}
673
674void GeneratorStore::VerifyInputs(MaglevGraphLabeller* graph_labeller) const {
675 for (int i = 0; i < input_count(); i++) {
676 CheckValueInputIs(this, i, ValueRepresentation::kTagged, graph_labeller);
677 }
678}

680void Phi::VerifyInputs(MaglevGraphLabeller* graph_labeller) const {
681 switch (value_representation()) {
682#define CASE_REPR(repr) \
683 case ValueRepresentation::k##repr: \
684 for (int i = 0; i < input_count(); i++) { \
685 CheckValueInputIs(this, i, ValueRepresentation::k##repr, \
686 graph_labeller); \
687 } \
688 break;
689
690 CASE_REPR(Tagged)
691 CASE_REPR(Int32)
692 CASE_REPR(Uint32)
693 CASE_REPR(Float64)
694 CASE_REPR(HoleyFloat64)
695#undef CASE_REPR
696 case ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
697 UNREACHABLE();
698 }
699}

831
832void CallBuiltin::VerifyInputs(MaglevGraphLabeller* graph_labeller) const {
833 auto descriptor = Builtins::CallInterfaceDescriptorFor(builtin());
834 int count = input_count();
835 // Verify context.
836 if (descriptor.HasContextParameter()) {
837 CheckValueInputIs(this, count - 1, ValueRepresentation::kTagged,
838 graph_labeller);
839 count--;
840 }
841
842// {all_input_count} includes the feedback slot and vector.
843#ifdef DEBUG
844 int all_input_count = count + (has_feedback() ? 2 : 0);
845 if (descriptor.AllowVarArgs()) {
846 DCHECK_GE(all_input_count, descriptor.GetParameterCount());
847 } else {
848 DCHECK_EQ(all_input_count, descriptor.GetParameterCount());
849 }
850#endif
851 int i = 0;
852 // Check the rest of inputs.
853 for (; i < count; ++i) {
854 MachineType type = i < descriptor.GetParameterCount()
855 ? descriptor.GetParameterType(i)
856 : MachineType::AnyTagged();
857 CheckValueInputIs(this, i, ToValueRepresentation(type), graph_labeller);
858 }
859}
860
861#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
862void CallBuiltin::MarkTaggedInputsAsDecompressing() {
863 auto descriptor = Builtins::CallInterfaceDescriptorFor(builtin());
864 int count = input_count();
865 // Set context.
866 if (descriptor.HasContextParameter()) {
867 input(count - 1).node()->SetTaggedResultNeedsDecompress();
868 count--;
869 }
870 int i = 0;
871 // Set the rest of the tagged inputs.
872 for (; i < count; ++i) {
873 MachineType type = i < descriptor.GetParameterCount()
874 ? descriptor.GetParameterType(i)
875 : MachineType::AnyTagged();
876 if (type.IsTagged() && !type.IsTaggedSigned()) {
877 input(i).node()->SetTaggedResultNeedsDecompress();
878 }
879 }
880}
881#endif

921Handle<Object> ValueNode::Reify(LocalIsolate* isolate) const {
922 switch (opcode()) {
923#define V(Name) \
924 case Opcode::k##Name: \
925 return this->Cast<Name>()->DoReify(isolate);
926 CONSTANT_VALUE_NODE_LIST(V)
927#undef V
928 default:
929 UNREACHABLE();
930 }
931}
932
933Handle<Object> ExternalConstant::DoReify(LocalIsolate* isolate) const {
934 UNREACHABLE();
935}
936
937Handle<Object> SmiConstant::DoReify(LocalIsolate* isolate) const {
938 return handle(value_, isolate);
939}
940
941Handle<Object> TaggedIndexConstant::DoReify(LocalIsolate* isolate) const {
942 UNREACHABLE();
943}
944
945Handle<Object> Int32Constant::DoReify(LocalIsolate* isolate) const {
946 return isolate->factory()->NewNumberFromInt<AllocationType::kOld>(value());
947}
948
949Handle<Object> Uint32Constant::DoReify(LocalIsolate* isolate) const {
950 return isolate->factory()->NewNumberFromUint<AllocationType::kOld>(value());
951}
952
953Handle<Object> Float64Constant::DoReify(LocalIsolate* isolate) const {
954 return isolate->factory()->NewNumber<AllocationType::kOld>(
955 value_.get_scalar());
956}
957
958Handle<Object> Constant::DoReify(LocalIsolate* isolate) const {
959 return object_.object();
960}
961
962Handle<Object> TrustedConstant::DoReify(LocalIsolate* isolate) const {
963 return object_.object();
964}
965
966Handle<Object> RootConstant::DoReify(LocalIsolate* isolate) const {
967 return isolate->root_handle(index());
968}

984namespace {
985template <typename NodeT>
986void LoadToRegisterHelper(NodeT* node, MaglevAssembler* masm, Register reg) {
987 if constexpr (!IsDoubleRepresentation(
988 NodeT::kProperties.value_representation())) {
989 return node->DoLoadToRegister(masm, reg);
990 } else {
991 UNREACHABLE();
992 }
993}
994template <typename NodeT>
995void LoadToRegisterHelper(NodeT* node, MaglevAssembler* masm,
996 DoubleRegister reg) {
997 if constexpr (IsDoubleRepresentation(
998 NodeT::kProperties.value_representation())) {
999 return node->DoLoadToRegister(masm, reg);
1000 } else {
1001 UNREACHABLE();
1002 }
1003}
1004} // namespace

1006void ValueNode::LoadToRegister(MaglevAssembler* masm, Register reg) {
1007 switch (opcode()) {
1008#define V(Name) \
1009 case Opcode::k##Name: \
1010 return LoadToRegisterHelper(this->Cast<Name>(), masm, reg);
1011 VALUE_NODE_LIST(V)
1012#undef V
1013 default:
1014 UNREACHABLE();
1015 }
1016}
1017void ValueNode::LoadToRegister(MaglevAssembler* masm, DoubleRegister reg) {
1018 switch (opcode()) {
1019#define V(Name) \
1020 case Opcode::k##Name: \
1021 return LoadToRegisterHelper(this->Cast<Name>(), masm, reg);
1022 VALUE_NODE_LIST(V)
1023#undef V
1024 default:
1025 UNREACHABLE();
1026 }
1027}

1029void ValueNode::DoLoadToRegister(MaglevAssembler* masm, Register reg) {
1030 DCHECK(is_spilled());
1031 DCHECK(!use_double_register());
1032 __ Move(reg,
1033 masm->GetStackSlot(compiler::AllocatedOperand::cast(spill_slot())));
1034}
1035
1036void ValueNode::DoLoadToRegister(MaglevAssembler* masm, DoubleRegister reg) {
1037 DCHECK(is_spilled());
1038 DCHECK(use_double_register());
1039 __ LoadFloat64(
1040 reg, masm->GetStackSlot(compiler::AllocatedOperand::cast(spill_slot())));
1041}

1148
1149int FunctionEntryStackCheck::MaxCallStackArgs() const { return 0; }
1150void FunctionEntryStackCheck::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
1151 set_temporaries_needed(2);
1152 // kReturnRegister0 should not be one of the available temporary registers.
1153 RequireSpecificTemporary(kReturnRegister0);
1154}
1155void FunctionEntryStackCheck::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
1156 const ProcessingState& state) {
1157 // Stack check. This folds the checks for both the interrupt stack limit
1158 // check and the real stack limit into one by just checking for the
1159 // interrupt limit. The interrupt limit is either equal to the real
1160 // stack limit or tighter. By ensuring we have space until that limit
1161 // after building the frame we can quickly precheck both at once.
1162 const int stack_check_offset = masm->code_gen_state()->stack_check_offset();
1163 // Only NewTarget can be live at this point.
1164 DCHECK_LE(register_snapshot().live_registers.Count(), 1);
1165 Builtin builtin =
1166 register_snapshot().live_tagged_registers.has(
1167 kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister)
1168 ? Builtin::kMaglevFunctionEntryStackCheck_WithNewTarget
1169 : Builtin::kMaglevFunctionEntryStackCheck_WithoutNewTarget;
1170 ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
1171 Condition cond = __ FunctionEntryStackCheck(stack_check_offset);
1172 if (masm->isolate()->is_short_builtin_calls_enabled()) {
1173 __ JumpIf(cond, *done, Label::kNear);
1174 __ Move(kReturnRegister0, Smi::FromInt(stack_check_offset));
1175 __ MacroAssembler::CallBuiltin(builtin);
1176 masm->DefineLazyDeoptPoint(lazy_deopt_info());
1177 } else {
1178 __ JumpToDeferredIf(
1179 NegateCondition(cond),
1180 [](MaglevAssembler* masm, ZoneLabelRef done,
1181 FunctionEntryStackCheck* node, Builtin builtin,
1182 int stack_check_offset) {
1183 __ Move(kReturnRegister0, Smi::FromInt(stack_check_offset));
1184 __ MacroAssembler::CallBuiltin(builtin);
1185 masm->DefineLazyDeoptPoint(node->lazy_deopt_info());
1186 __ Jump(*done);
1187 },
1188 done, this, builtin, stack_check_offset);
1189 }
1190 __ bind(*done);
1191}

1201void GetSecondReturnedValue::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
1202 DefineAsFixed(this, kReturnRegister1);
1203}
1204void GetSecondReturnedValue::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
1205 const ProcessingState& state) {
1206 // No-op. This is just a hack that binds kReturnRegister1 to a value node.
1207 // kReturnRegister1 is guaranteed to be free in the register allocator, since
1208 // previous node in the basic block is a call.
1209#ifdef DEBUG
1210 // Check if the previous node is call.
1211 Node* previous = nullptr;
1212 for (Node* node : state.block()->nodes()) {
1213 if (node == this) {
1214 break;
1215 }
1216 previous = node;
1217 }
1218 DCHECK_NE(previous, nullptr);
1219 DCHECK(previous->properties().is_call());
1220#endif // DEBUG
1221}

1228void Phi::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
1229 for (Input& input : *this) {
1230 UseAny(input);
1231 }
1232
1233 // We have to pass a policy for the result, but it is ignored during register
1234 // allocation. See StraightForwardRegisterAllocator::AllocateRegisters which
1235 // has special handling for Phis.
1236 static const compiler::UnallocatedOperand::ExtendedPolicy kIgnoredPolicy =
1237 compiler::UnallocatedOperand::REGISTER_OR_SLOT_OR_CONSTANT;
1238
1239 result().SetUnallocated(kIgnoredPolicy, kNoVreg);
1240}

1243
1244void ArgumentsElements::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
1245 using SloppyArgsD =
1246 CallInterfaceDescriptorFor<Builtin::kNewSloppyArgumentsElements>::type;
1247 using StrictArgsD =
1248 CallInterfaceDescriptorFor<Builtin::kNewStrictArgumentsElements>::type;
1249 using RestArgsD =
1250 CallInterfaceDescriptorFor<Builtin::kNewRestArgumentsElements>::type;
1251 static_assert(
1252 SloppyArgsD::GetRegisterParameter(SloppyArgsD::kArgumentCount) ==
1253 StrictArgsD::GetRegisterParameter(StrictArgsD::kArgumentCount));
1254 static_assert(
1255 SloppyArgsD::GetRegisterParameter(SloppyArgsD::kArgumentCount) ==
1256 StrictArgsD::GetRegisterParameter(RestArgsD::kArgumentCount));
1257 UseFixed(arguments_count_input(),
1258 SloppyArgsD::GetRegisterParameter(SloppyArgsD::kArgumentCount));
1259 DefineAsFixed(this, kReturnRegister0);
1260}
1261
1262void ArgumentsElements::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
1263 const ProcessingState& state) {
1264 Register arguments_count = ToRegister(arguments_count_input());
1265 switch (type()) {
1266 case CreateArgumentsType::kMappedArguments:
1267 __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kNewSloppyArgumentsElements>(
1268 __ GetFramePointer(), formal_parameter_count(), arguments_count);
1269 break;
1270 case CreateArgumentsType::kUnmappedArguments:
1271 __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kNewStrictArgumentsElements>(
1272 __ GetFramePointer(), formal_parameter_count(), arguments_count);
1273 break;
1274 case CreateArgumentsType::kRestParameter:
1275 __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kNewRestArgumentsElements>(
1276 __ GetFramePointer(), formal_parameter_count(), arguments_count);
1277 break;
1278 }
1279}
1280
1281void AllocateElementsArray::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
1282 UseAndClobberRegister(length_input());
1283 DefineAsRegister(this);
1284 set_temporaries_needed(1);
1285}
1286void AllocateElementsArray::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
1287 const ProcessingState& state) {
1288 Register length = ToRegister(length_input());
1289 Register elements = ToRegister(result());
1290 Label allocate_elements, done;
1291 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
1292 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1293 // Be sure to save the length in the register snapshot.
1294 RegisterSnapshot snapshot = register_snapshot();
1295 snapshot.live_registers.set(length);
1296
1297 // Return empty fixed array if length equal zero.
1298 __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(length, 0, kNotEqual, &allocate_elements,
1299 Label::Distance::kNear);
1300 __ LoadRoot(elements, RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray);
1301 __ Jump(&done);
1302
1303 // Allocate a fixed array object.
1304 __ bind(&allocate_elements);
1305 __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(
1306 length, JSArray::kInitialMaxFastElementArray, kGreaterThanEqual,
1307 __ GetDeoptLabel(this,
1308 DeoptimizeReason::kGreaterThanMaxFastElementArray));
1309 {
1310 Register size_in_bytes = scratch;
1311 __ Move(size_in_bytes, length);
1312 __ ShiftLeft(size_in_bytes, kTaggedSizeLog2);
1313 __ AddInt32(size_in_bytes, OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray));
1314 __ Allocate(snapshot, elements, size_in_bytes, allocation_type_);
1315 __ SetMapAsRoot(elements, RootIndex::kFixedArrayMap);
1316 }
1317 {
1318 Register smi_length = scratch;
1319 __ UncheckedSmiTagInt32(smi_length, length);
1320 __ StoreTaggedFieldNoWriteBarrier(elements, offsetof(FixedArray, length_),
1321 smi_length);
1322 }
1323
1324 // Initialize the array with holes.
1325 {
1326 Label loop;
1327 Register the_hole = scratch;
1328 __ LoadTaggedRoot(the_hole, RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
1329 __ bind(&loop);
1330 __ DecrementInt32(length);
1331 // TODO(victorgomes): This can be done more efficiently by have the root
1332 // (the_hole) as an immediate in the store.
1333 __ StoreFixedArrayElementNoWriteBarrier(elements, length, the_hole);
1334 __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(length, 0, kGreaterThan, &loop,
1335 Label::Distance::kNear);
1336 }
1337 __ bind(&done);
1338}

1342constexpr Builtin BuiltinFor(Operation operation) {
1343 switch (operation) {
1344#define CASE(name) \
1345 case Operation::k##name: \
1346 return Builtin::k##name##_WithFeedback;
1347 OPERATION_LIST(CASE)
1348#undef CASE
1349 }
1350}

1355void UnaryWithFeedbackNode<Derived, kOperation>::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
1356 using D = UnaryOp_WithFeedbackDescriptor;
1357 UseFixed(operand_input(), D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kValue));
1358 DefineAsFixed(this, kReturnRegister0);
1359}

1363 MaglevAssembler* masm, const ProcessingState& state) {
1364 __ CallBuiltin<BuiltinFor(kOperation)>(
1365 masm->native_context().object(), // context
1366 operand_input(), // value
1367 feedback().index(), // feedback slot
1368 feedback().vector // feedback vector
1369 );
1370 masm->DefineExceptionHandlerAndLazyDeoptPoint(this);
1371}

1396 void Name::SetValueLocationConstraints() { \
1397 Base::SetValueLocationConstraints(); \
1398 } \
1399 void Name::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm, \
1400 const ProcessingState& state) { \
1401 Base::GenerateCode(masm, state); \
1402 }

1408namespace {
1409template <typename T>
1410struct GetRegister;
1411template <>
1412struct GetRegister<Register> {
1413 static Register Get(compiler::AllocatedOperand target) {
1414 return target.GetRegister();
1415 }
1416};
1417template <>
1418struct GetRegister<DoubleRegister> {
1419 static DoubleRegister Get(compiler::AllocatedOperand target) {
1420 return target.GetDoubleRegister();
1421 }
1422};
1423} // namespace
1424
1425void ConstantGapMove::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
1426 const ProcessingState& state) {
1427 switch (node_->opcode()) {
1428#define CASE(Name) \
1429 case Opcode::k##Name: \
1430 return node_->Cast<Name>()->DoLoadToRegister( \
1431 masm, GetRegister<Name::OutputRegister>::Get(target()));
1432 CONSTANT_VALUE_NODE_LIST(CASE)
1433#undef CASE
1434 default:
1435 UNREACHABLE();
1436 }
1437}
1438
1439void GapMove::SetValueLocationConstraints() { UNREACHABLE(); }
1440void GapMove::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
1441 const ProcessingState& state) {
1442 DCHECK_EQ(source().representation(), target().representation());
1443 MachineRepresentation repr = source().representation();
1444 if (source().IsRegister()) {
1445 Register source_reg = ToRegister(source());
1446 if (target().IsAnyRegister()) {
1447 DCHECK(target().IsRegister());
1448 __ MoveRepr(repr, ToRegister(target()), source_reg);
1449 } else {
1450 __ MoveRepr(repr, masm->ToMemOperand(target()), source_reg);
1451 }
1452 } else if (source().IsDoubleRegister()) {
1453 DoubleRegister source_reg = ToDoubleRegister(source());
1454 if (target().IsAnyRegister()) {
1455 DCHECK(target().IsDoubleRegister());
1456 __ Move(ToDoubleRegister(target()), source_reg);
1457 } else {
1458 __ StoreFloat64(masm->ToMemOperand(target()), source_reg);
1459 }
1460 } else {
1461 DCHECK(source().IsAnyStackSlot());
1462 MemOperand source_op = masm->ToMemOperand(source());
1463 if (target().IsRegister()) {
1464 __ MoveRepr(MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer, ToRegister(target()),
1465 source_op);
1466 } else if (target().IsDoubleRegister()) {
1467 __ LoadFloat64(ToDoubleRegister(target()), source_op);
1468 } else {
1469 DCHECK(target().IsAnyStackSlot());
1470 DCHECK_EQ(ElementSizeInBytes(repr), kSystemPointerSize);
1471 __ MoveRepr(repr, masm->ToMemOperand(target()), source_op);
1472 }
1473 }
1474}

1653namespace {
1654
1655void JumpToFailIfNotHeapNumberOrOddball(
1656 MaglevAssembler* masm, Register value,
1657 TaggedToFloat64ConversionType conversion_type, Label* fail) {
1658 if (!fail && !v8_flags.debug_code) return;
1659
1660 static_assert(InstanceType::HEAP_NUMBER_TYPE + 1 ==
1661 InstanceType::ODDBALL_TYPE);
1662 switch (conversion_type) {
1663 case TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kNumberOrBoolean: {
1664 // Check if HeapNumber or Boolean, jump to fail otherwise.
1665 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
1666 Register map = temps.AcquireScratch();
1667
1668#if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
1669 static_assert(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kBooleanMap + Map::kSize ==
1670 StaticReadOnlyRoot::kHeapNumberMap);
1671 __ LoadMapForCompare(map, value);
1672 if (fail) {
1673 __ JumpIfObjectNotInRange(map, StaticReadOnlyRoot::kBooleanMap,
1674 StaticReadOnlyRoot::kHeapNumberMap, fail);
1675 } else {
1676 __ AssertObjectInRange(map, StaticReadOnlyRoot::kBooleanMap,
1677 StaticReadOnlyRoot::kHeapNumberMap,
1678 AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
1679 }
1680#else
1681 Label done;
1682 __ LoadMap(map, value);
1683 __ CompareRoot(map, RootIndex::kHeapNumberMap);
1684 __ JumpIf(kEqual, &done);
1685 __ CompareRoot(map, RootIndex::kBooleanMap);
1686 if (fail) {
1687 __ JumpIf(kNotEqual, fail);
1688 } else {
1689 __ Assert(kEqual, AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
1690 }
1691 __ bind(&done);
1692#endif
1693 break;
1694 }
1695 case TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kNumberOrOddball:
1696 // Check if HeapNumber or Oddball, jump to fail otherwise.
1697 if (fail) {
1698 __ JumpIfObjectTypeNotInRange(value, InstanceType::HEAP_NUMBER_TYPE,
1699 InstanceType::ODDBALL_TYPE, fail);
1700 } else {
1701 __ AssertObjectTypeInRange(value, InstanceType::HEAP_NUMBER_TYPE,
1702 InstanceType::ODDBALL_TYPE,
1703 AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
1704 }
1705 break;
1706 case TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kOnlyNumber:
1707 // Check if HeapNumber, jump to fail otherwise.
1708 if (fail) {
1709 __ JumpIfNotObjectType(value, InstanceType::HEAP_NUMBER_TYPE, fail);
1710 } else {
1711 __ AssertObjectType(value, InstanceType::HEAP_NUMBER_TYPE,
1712 AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
1713 }
1714 break;
1715 }
1716}
1717
1718void TryUnboxNumberOrOddball(MaglevAssembler* masm, DoubleRegister dst,
1719 Register clobbered_src,
1720 TaggedToFloat64ConversionType conversion_type,
1721 Label* fail) {
1722 Label is_not_smi, done;
1723 // Check if Smi.
1724 __ JumpIfNotSmi(clobbered_src, &is_not_smi, Label::kNear);
1725 // If Smi, convert to Float64.
1726 __ SmiToInt32(clobbered_src);
1727 __ Int32ToDouble(dst, clobbered_src);
1728 __ Jump(&done);
1729 __ bind(&is_not_smi);
1730 JumpToFailIfNotHeapNumberOrOddball(masm, clobbered_src, conversion_type,
1731 fail);
1732 __ LoadHeapNumberOrOddballValue(dst, clobbered_src);
1733 __ bind(&done);
1734}

1768void CheckedNumberToInt32::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
1769 UseRegister(input());
1770 DefineAsRegister(this);
1771 set_double_temporaries_needed(1);

1773void CheckedNumberToInt32::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
1774 const ProcessingState& state) {
1775 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
1776 DoubleRegister double_value = temps.AcquireDouble();
1777 Register value = ToRegister(input());
1778 Label is_not_smi, done;
1779 Label* deopt_label = __ GetDeoptLabel(this, DeoptimizeReason::kNotInt32);
1780 // Check if Smi.
1781 __ JumpIfNotSmi(value, &is_not_smi, Label::kNear);
1782 __ SmiToInt32(ToRegister(result()), value);
1783 __ Jump(&done);
1784 __ bind(&is_not_smi);
1785 // Check if Number.
1786 JumpToFailIfNotHeapNumberOrOddball(
1787 masm, value, TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kOnlyNumber, deopt_label);
1788 __ LoadHeapNumberValue(double_value, value);
1789 __ TryTruncateDoubleToInt32(ToRegister(result()), double_value, deopt_label);
1790 __ bind(&done);
1791}

1793namespace {
1794
1795void EmitTruncateNumberOrOddballToInt32(
1796 MaglevAssembler* masm, Register value, Register result_reg,
1797 TaggedToFloat64ConversionType conversion_type, Label* not_a_number) {
1798 Label is_not_smi, done;
1799 // Check if Smi.
1800 __ JumpIfNotSmi(value, &is_not_smi, Label::kNear);
1801 // If Smi, convert to Int32.
1802 __ SmiToInt32(value);
1803 __ Jump(&done, Label::kNear);
1804 __ bind(&is_not_smi);
1805 JumpToFailIfNotHeapNumberOrOddball(masm, value, conversion_type,
1806 not_a_number);
1807 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
1808 DoubleRegister double_value = temps.AcquireScratchDouble();
1809 __ LoadHeapNumberOrOddballValue(double_value, value);
1810 __ TruncateDoubleToInt32(result_reg, double_value);
1811 __ bind(&done);
1812}

1815
1816void CheckedObjectToIndex::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
1817 UseRegister(object_input());
1818 DefineAsRegister(this);
1819 set_double_temporaries_needed(1);
1820}
1821void CheckedObjectToIndex::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
1822 const ProcessingState& state) {
1823 Register object = ToRegister(object_input());
1824 Register result_reg = ToRegister(result());
1825 ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
1826 __ JumpIfNotSmi(
1827 object,
1828 __ MakeDeferredCode(
1829 [](MaglevAssembler* masm, Register object, Register result_reg,
1830 ZoneLabelRef done, CheckedObjectToIndex* node) {
1831 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
1832 Register map = temps.AcquireScratch();
1833 Label check_string;
1834 __ LoadMapForCompare(map, object);
1835 __ JumpIfNotRoot(
1836 map, RootIndex::kHeapNumberMap, &check_string,
1837 v8_flags.deopt_every_n_times > 0 ? Label::kFar : Label::kNear);
1838 {
1839 DoubleRegister number_value = temps.AcquireDouble();
1840 __ LoadHeapNumberValue(number_value, object);
1841 __ TryChangeFloat64ToIndex(
1842 result_reg, number_value, *done,
1843 __ GetDeoptLabel(node, DeoptimizeReason::kNotInt32));
1844 }
1845 __ bind(&check_string);
1846 // The IC will go generic if it encounters something other than a
1847 // Number or String key.
1848 __ JumpIfStringMap(
1849 map, __ GetDeoptLabel(node, DeoptimizeReason::kNotInt32),
1850 Label::kFar, false);
1851 // map is clobbered after this call.
1852
1853 {
1854 // TODO(verwaest): Load the cached number from the string hash.
1855 RegisterSnapshot snapshot = node->register_snapshot();
1856 snapshot.live_registers.clear(result_reg);
1857 DCHECK(!snapshot.live_tagged_registers.has(result_reg));
1858 {
1859 SaveRegisterStateForCall save_register_state(masm, snapshot);
1860 AllowExternalCallThatCantCauseGC scope(masm);
1861 __ PrepareCallCFunction(1);
1862 __ Move(kCArgRegs[0], object);
1863 __ CallCFunction(
1864 ExternalReference::string_to_array_index_function(), 1);
1865 // No need for safepoint since this is a fast C call.
1866 __ Move(result_reg, kReturnRegister0);
1867 }
1868 __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(
1869 result_reg, 0, kLessThan,
1870 __ GetDeoptLabel(node, DeoptimizeReason::kNotInt32));
1871 __ Jump(*done);
1872 }
1873 },
1874 object, result_reg, done, this));
1875
1876 // If we didn't enter the deferred block, we're a Smi.
1877 __ SmiToInt32(result_reg, object);
1878 __ bind(*done);
1879}

1926
1927void CheckMaps::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
1928 UseRegister(receiver_input());
1929 set_temporaries_needed(MapCompare::TemporaryCount(maps_.size()));
1930}
1931
1932void CheckMaps::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
1933 const ProcessingState& state) {
1934 Register object = ToRegister(receiver_input());
1935
1936 // We emit an unconditional deopt if we intersect the map sets and the
1937 // intersection is empty.
1938 DCHECK(!maps().is_empty());
1939
1940 bool maps_include_heap_number = compiler::AnyMapIsHeapNumber(maps());
1941
1942 // Experimentally figured out map limit (with slack) which allows us to use
1943 // near jumps in the code below. If --deopt-every-n-times is on, we generate
1944 // a bit more code, so disable the near jump optimization.
1945 constexpr int kMapCountForNearJumps = kTaggedSize == 4 ? 10 : 5;
1946 Label::Distance jump_distance = (maps().size() <= kMapCountForNearJumps &&
1947 v8_flags.deopt_every_n_times <= 0)
1948 ? Label::Distance::kNear
1949 : Label::Distance::kFar;
1950
1951 Label done;
1952 if (check_type() == CheckType::kOmitHeapObjectCheck) {
1953 __ AssertNotSmi(object);
1954 } else {
1955 if (maps_include_heap_number) {
1956 // Smis count as matching the HeapNumber map, so we're done.
1957 __ JumpIfSmi(object, &done, jump_distance);
1958 } else {
1959 __ EmitEagerDeoptIfSmi(this, object, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap);
1960 }
1961 }
1962
1963 MapCompare map_compare(masm, object, maps_.size());
1964 size_t map_count = maps().size();
1965 for (size_t i = 0; i < map_count - 1; ++i) {
1966 Handle<Map> map = maps().at(i).object();
1967 map_compare.Generate(map, kEqual, &done, jump_distance);
1968 }
1969 Handle<Map> last_map = maps().at(map_count - 1).object();
1970 Label* fail = __ GetDeoptLabel(this, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap);
1971 map_compare.Generate(last_map, kNotEqual, fail);
1972 __ bind(&done);
1973}
1974
1975int CheckMapsWithMigrationAndDeopt::MaxCallStackArgs() const {
1976 DCHECK_EQ(Runtime::FunctionForId(
1977 Runtime::kTryMigrateInstanceAndMarkMapAsMigrationTarget)
1978 ->nargs,
1979 1);
1980 return 1;
1981}
1982
1983void CheckMapsWithMigrationAndDeopt::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
1984 UseRegister(receiver_input());
1985 set_temporaries_needed(MapCompare::TemporaryCount(maps_.size()));
1986}
1987
1988void CheckMapsWithMigrationAndDeopt::GenerateCode(
1989 MaglevAssembler* masm, const ProcessingState& state) {
1990 Register object = ToRegister(receiver_input());
1991
1992 // We emit an unconditional deopt if we intersect the map sets and the
1993 // intersection is empty.
1994 DCHECK(!maps().is_empty());
1995
1996 bool maps_include_heap_number = compiler::AnyMapIsHeapNumber(maps());
1997
1998 // Experimentally figured out map limit (with slack) which allows us to use
1999 // near jumps in the code below. If --deopt-every-n-times is on, we generate
2000 // a bit more code, so disable the near jump optimization.
2001 constexpr int kMapCountForNearJumps = kTaggedSize == 4 ? 10 : 5;
2002 Label::Distance jump_distance = (maps().size() <= kMapCountForNearJumps &&
2003 v8_flags.deopt_every_n_times <= 0)
2004 ? Label::Distance::kNear
2005 : Label::Distance::kFar;
2006
2007 Label done;
2008 if (check_type() == CheckType::kOmitHeapObjectCheck) {
2009 __ AssertNotSmi(object);
2010 } else {
2011 if (maps_include_heap_number) {
2012 // Smis count as matching the HeapNumber map, so we're done.
2013 __ JumpIfSmi(object, &done, jump_distance);
2014 } else {
2015 __ EmitEagerDeoptIfSmi(this, object, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap);
2016 }
2017 }
2018
2019 MapCompare map_compare(masm, object, maps_.size());
2020 size_t map_count = maps().size();
2021 for (size_t i = 0; i < map_count - 1; ++i) {
2022 Handle<Map> map = maps().at(i).object();
2023 map_compare.Generate(map, kEqual, &done, jump_distance);
2024 }
2025
2026 Handle<Map> last_map = maps().at(map_count - 1).object();
2027 map_compare.Generate(
2028 last_map, kNotEqual,
2029 __ MakeDeferredCode(
2030 [](MaglevAssembler* masm, RegisterSnapshot register_snapshot,
2031 MapCompare map_compare, CheckMapsWithMigrationAndDeopt* node) {
2032 Label* deopt = __ GetDeoptLabel(node, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap);
2033 // If the map is not deprecated, we fail the map check.
2034 __ TestInt32AndJumpIfAllClear(
2035 FieldMemOperand(map_compare.GetMap(), Map::kBitField3Offset),
2036 Map::Bits3::IsDeprecatedBit::kMask, deopt);
2037
2038 // Otherwise, try migrating the object.
2039 __ TryMigrateInstanceAndMarkMapAsMigrationTarget(
2040 map_compare.GetObject(), register_snapshot);
2041 // Deopt even if the migration was successful.
2042 __ JumpToDeopt(deopt);
2043 },
2044 register_snapshot(), map_compare, this));
2045 // If the jump to deferred code was not taken, the map was equal to the
2046 // last map.
2047 __ bind(&done);
2048}
2049
2050int CheckMapsWithMigration::MaxCallStackArgs() const {
2051 DCHECK_EQ(Runtime::FunctionForId(Runtime::kTryMigrateInstance)->nargs, 1);
2052 return 1;
2053}
2054
2055void CheckMapsWithMigration::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
2056 UseRegister(receiver_input());
2057 set_temporaries_needed(MapCompare::TemporaryCount(maps_.size()));
2058}
2059
2060void CheckMapsWithMigration::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
2061 const ProcessingState& state) {
2062 // We emit an unconditional deopt if we intersect the map sets and the
2063 // intersection is empty.
2064 DCHECK(!maps().is_empty());
2065
2066 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
2067 Register object = ToRegister(receiver_input());
2068
2069 bool maps_include_heap_number = compiler::AnyMapIsHeapNumber(maps());
2070
2071 ZoneLabelRef map_checks(masm), done(masm);
2072
2073 if (check_type() == CheckType::kOmitHeapObjectCheck) {
2074 __ AssertNotSmi(object);
2075 } else {
2076 if (maps_include_heap_number) {
2077 // Smis count as matching the HeapNumber map, so we're done.
2078 __ JumpIfSmi(object, *done);
2079 } else {
2080 __ EmitEagerDeoptIfSmi(this, object, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap);
2081 }
2082 }
2083
2084 // If we jump from here from the deferred code (below), we need to reload
2085 // the map.
2086 __ bind(*map_checks);
2087
2088 RegisterSnapshot save_registers = register_snapshot();
2089 // Make sure that the object register is not clobbered by the
2090 // Runtime::kMigrateInstance runtime call. It's ok to clobber the register
2091 // where the object map is, since the map is reloaded after the runtime call.
2092 save_registers.live_registers.set(object);
2093 save_registers.live_tagged_registers.set(object);
2094
2095 size_t map_count = maps().size();
2096 bool has_migration_targets = false;
2097 MapCompare map_compare(masm, object, maps_.size());
2098 Handle<Map> map_handle;
2099 for (size_t i = 0; i < map_count; ++i) {
2100 map_handle = maps().at(i).object();
2101 const bool last_map = (i == map_count - 1);
2102 if (!last_map) {
2103 map_compare.Generate(map_handle, kEqual, *done);
2104 }
2105 if (map_handle->is_migration_target()) {
2106 has_migration_targets = true;
2107 }
2108 }
2109
2110 if (!has_migration_targets) {
2111 // Emit deopt for the last map.
2112 map_compare.Generate(map_handle, kNotEqual,
2113 __ GetDeoptLabel(this, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap));
2114 } else {
2115 map_compare.Generate(
2116 map_handle, kNotEqual,
2117 __ MakeDeferredCode(
2118 [](MaglevAssembler* masm, RegisterSnapshot register_snapshot,
2119 ZoneLabelRef map_checks, MapCompare map_compare,
2120 CheckMapsWithMigration* node) {
2121 Label* deopt =
2122 __ GetDeoptLabel(node, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap);
2123 // If the map is not deprecated, we fail the map check.
2124 __ TestInt32AndJumpIfAllClear(
2125 FieldMemOperand(map_compare.GetMap(), Map::kBitField3Offset),
2126 Map::Bits3::IsDeprecatedBit::kMask, deopt);
2127
2128 // Otherwise, try migrating the object.
2129 __ TryMigrateInstance(map_compare.GetObject(), register_snapshot,
2130 deopt);
2131 __ Jump(*map_checks);
2132 // We'll need to reload the map since it might have changed; it's
2133 // done right after the map_checks label.
2134 },
2135 save_registers, map_checks, map_compare, this));
2136 // If the jump to deferred code was not taken, the map was equal to the
2137 // last map.
2138 } // End of the `has_migration_targets` case.
2139 __ bind(*done);
2140}

2142void CheckMapsWithAlreadyLoadedMap::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
2143 UseRegister(object_input());
2144 UseRegister(map_input());
2145}
2146
2147void CheckMapsWithAlreadyLoadedMap::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
2148 const ProcessingState& state) {
2149 Register map = ToRegister(map_input());
2150
2151 // We emit an unconditional deopt if we intersect the map sets and the
2152 // intersection is empty.
2153 DCHECK(!maps().is_empty());
2154
2155 // CheckMapsWithAlreadyLoadedMap can only be used in contexts where SMIs /
2156 // HeapNumbers don't make sense (e.g., if we're loading properties from them).
2157 DCHECK(!compiler::AnyMapIsHeapNumber(maps()));
2158
2159 // Experimentally figured out map limit (with slack) which allows us to use
2160 // near jumps in the code below. If --deopt-every-n-times is on, we generate
2161 // a bit more code, so disable the near jump optimization.
2162 constexpr int kMapCountForNearJumps = kTaggedSize == 4 ? 10 : 5;
2163 Label::Distance jump_distance = (maps().size() <= kMapCountForNearJumps &&
2164 v8_flags.deopt_every_n_times <= 0)
2165 ? Label::Distance::kNear
2166 : Label::Distance::kFar;
2167
2168 Label done;
2169 size_t map_count = maps().size();
2170 for (size_t i = 0; i < map_count - 1; ++i) {
2171 Handle<Map> map_at_i = maps().at(i).object();
2172 __ CompareTaggedAndJumpIf(map, map_at_i, kEqual, &done, jump_distance);
2173 }
2174 Handle<Map> last_map = maps().at(map_count - 1).object();
2175 Label* fail = __ GetDeoptLabel(this, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap);
2176 __ CompareTaggedAndJumpIf(map, last_map, kNotEqual, fail);
2177 __ bind(&done);
2178}

2180int MigrateMapIfNeeded::MaxCallStackArgs() const {
2181 DCHECK_EQ(Runtime::FunctionForId(Runtime::kTryMigrateInstance)->nargs, 1);
2182 return 1;
2183}
2184
2185void MigrateMapIfNeeded::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
2186 UseRegister(map_input());
2187 UseRegister(object_input());
2188 DefineSameAsFirst(this);
2189}
2190
2191void MigrateMapIfNeeded::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
2192 const ProcessingState& state) {
2193 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
2194 Register object = ToRegister(object_input());
2195 Register map = ToRegister(map_input());
2196 DCHECK_EQ(map, ToRegister(result()));
2197
2198 ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
2199
2200 RegisterSnapshot save_registers = register_snapshot();
2201 // Make sure that the object register are not clobbered by TryMigrateInstance
2202 // (which does a runtime call). We need the object register for reloading the
2203 // map. It's okay to clobber the map register, since we will always reload (or
2204 // deopt) after the runtime call.
2205 save_registers.live_registers.set(object);
2206 save_registers.live_tagged_registers.set(object);
2207
2208 // If the map is deprecated, jump to the deferred code which will migrate it.
2209 __ TestInt32AndJumpIfAnySet(
2210 FieldMemOperand(map, Map::kBitField3Offset),
2211 Map::Bits3::IsDeprecatedBit::kMask,
2212 __ MakeDeferredCode(
2213 [](MaglevAssembler* masm, RegisterSnapshot register_snapshot,
2214 ZoneLabelRef done, Register object, Register map,
2215 MigrateMapIfNeeded* node) {
2216 Label* deopt = __ GetDeoptLabel(node, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap);
2217 __ TryMigrateInstance(object, register_snapshot, deopt);
2218 // Reload the map since TryMigrateInstance might have changed it.
2219 __ LoadTaggedField(map, object, HeapObject::kMapOffset);
2220 __ Jump(*done);
2221 },
2222 save_registers, done, object, map, this));
2223
2224 // No migration needed. Return the original map. We already have it in the
2225 // first input register which is the same as the return register.
2226
2227 __ bind(*done);
2228}

2330void Int32Compare::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
2331 const ProcessingState& state) {
2332 Register result = ToRegister(this->result());
2333 Label is_true, end;
2334 if (Int32Constant* constant =
2335 right_input().node()->TryCast<Int32Constant>()) {
2336 int32_t right_value = constant->value();
2337 __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(ToRegister(left_input()), right_value,
2338 ConditionFor(operation()), &is_true,
2339 Label::Distance::kNear);
2340 } else {
2341 __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(
2342 ToRegister(left_input()), ToRegister(right_input()),
2343 ConditionFor(operation()), &is_true, Label::Distance::kNear);
2344 }
2345 // TODO(leszeks): Investigate loading existing materialisations of roots here,
2346 // if available.
2347 __ LoadRoot(result, RootIndex::kFalseValue);
2348 __ jmp(&end);
2349 {
2350 __ bind(&is_true);
2351 __ LoadRoot(result, RootIndex::kTrueValue);
2352 }
2353 __ bind(&end);

2515void LoadTaggedFieldForScriptContextSlot::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
2516 UseRegister(context());
2517 set_temporaries_needed(2);
2518 set_double_temporaries_needed(1);
2519 DefineAsRegister(this);
2520}
2521
2522void LoadTaggedFieldForScriptContextSlot::GenerateCode(
2523 MaglevAssembler* masm, const ProcessingState& state) {
2524 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
2525 Register script_context = ToRegister(context());
2526 Register value = ToRegister(result());
2527 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2528 ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
2529 __ AssertObjectType(script_context, SCRIPT_CONTEXT_TYPE,
2530 AbortReason::kUnexpectedInstanceType);
2531
2532 // Be sure to not clobber script_context.
2533 if (value == script_context) {
2534 Register tmp = temps.Acquire();
2535 __ Move(tmp, script_context);
2536 script_context = tmp;
2537 }
2538
2539 // Load value from context.
2540 __ LoadTaggedField(value, script_context, offset());
2541
2542 // Check side table if HeapNumber.
2543 __ JumpIfSmi(value, *done);
2544 __ CompareMapWithRoot(value, RootIndex::kHeapNumberMap, scratch);
2545 __ JumpToDeferredIf(
2546 kEqual,
2547 [](MaglevAssembler* masm, Register script_context, Register result_reg,
2548 Register scratch, LoadTaggedFieldForScriptContextSlot* node,
2549 ZoneLabelRef done) {
2550 Label property_loaded;
2551 Label check_heap_number, allocate;
2552 // Load side table.
2553 // TODO(victorgomes): Should we hoist the side_table?
2554 __ LoadTaggedField(scratch, script_context,
2555 Context::OffsetOfElementAt(
2556 Context::CONTEXT_SIDE_TABLE_PROPERTY_INDEX));
2557 __ LoadTaggedField(
2558 scratch, scratch,
2559 FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(node->index() -
2560 Context::MIN_CONTEXT_EXTENDED_SLOTS));
2561
2562 __ JumpIfSmi(scratch, &property_loaded);
2563 __ AssertObjectType(scratch, CONTEXT_SIDE_PROPERTY_CELL_TYPE,
2564 AbortReason::kUnexpectedInstanceType);
2565 __ LoadTaggedField(scratch, scratch,
2566 ContextSidePropertyCell::kPropertyDetailsRawOffset);
2567 __ bind(&property_loaded);
2568
2569 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
2570 DoubleRegister double_value = temps.AcquireDouble();
2571
2572 if (v8_flags.script_context_mutable_heap_int32) {
2573 __ CompareTaggedAndJumpIf(scratch,
2574 ContextSidePropertyCell::MutableInt32(),
2575 kNotEqual, &check_heap_number);
2576 __ LoadHeapInt32Value(scratch, result_reg);
2577 __ Int32ToDouble(double_value, scratch);
2578 __ Jump(&allocate, Label::kNear);
2579 }
2580
2581 __ bind(&check_heap_number);
2582 __ CompareTaggedAndJumpIf(scratch,
2583 ContextSidePropertyCell::MutableHeapNumber(),
2584 kNotEqual, *done);
2585 __ LoadHeapNumberValue(double_value, result_reg);
2586
2587 __ bind(&allocate);
2588 __ AllocateHeapNumber(node->register_snapshot(), result_reg,
2589 double_value);
2590 __ Jump(*done);
2591 },
2592 script_context, value, scratch, this, done);
2593
2594 __ bind(*done);
2595}
2596
2597void LoadTaggedFieldByFieldIndex::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
2598 UseRegister(object_input());
2599 UseAndClobberRegister(index_input());
2600 DefineAsRegister(this);
2601 set_temporaries_needed(1);
2602 set_double_temporaries_needed(1);
2603}
2604void LoadTaggedFieldByFieldIndex::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
2605 const ProcessingState& state) {
2606 Register object = ToRegister(object_input());
2607 Register field_index = ToRegister(index_input());
2608 Register result_reg = ToRegister(result());
2609 __ AssertNotSmi(object);
2610 __ AssertSmi(field_index);
2611
2612 ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
2613
2614 // For in-object properties, the field_index is encoded as:
2615 //
2616 // field_index = array_index | is_double_bit | smi_tag
2617 // = array_index << (1+kSmiTagBits)
2618 // + is_double_bit << kSmiTagBits
2619 //
2620 // The value we want is at the field offset:
2621 //
2622 // (array_index << kTaggedSizeLog2) + JSObject::kHeaderSize
2623 //
2624 // We could get field_index from array_index by shifting away the double bit
2625 // and smi tag, followed by shifting back up again, but this means shifting
2626 // twice:
2627 //
2628 // ((field_index >> kSmiTagBits >> 1) << kTaggedSizeLog2
2629 // + JSObject::kHeaderSize
2630 //
2631 // Instead, we can do some rearranging to get the offset with either a single
2632 // small shift, or no shift at all:
2633 //
2634 // (array_index << kTaggedSizeLog2) + JSObject::kHeaderSize
2635 //
2636 // [Split shift to match array_index component of field_index]
2637 // = (
2638 // (array_index << 1+kSmiTagBits)) << (kTaggedSizeLog2-1-kSmiTagBits)
2639 // ) + JSObject::kHeaderSize
2640 //
2641 // [Substitute in field_index]
2642 // = (
2643 // (field_index - is_double_bit << kSmiTagBits)
2644 // << (kTaggedSizeLog2-1-kSmiTagBits)
2645 // ) + JSObject::kHeaderSize
2646 //
2647 // [Fold together the constants]
2648 // = (field_index << (kTaggedSizeLog2-1-kSmiTagBits)
2649 // + (JSObject::kHeaderSize - (is_double_bit << (kTaggedSizeLog2-1)))
2650 //
2651 // Note that this results in:
2652 //
2653 // * No shift when kSmiTagBits == kTaggedSizeLog2 - 1, which is the case
2654 // when pointer compression is on.
2655 // * A shift of 1 when kSmiTagBits == 1 and kTaggedSizeLog2 == 3, which
2656 // is the case when pointer compression is off but Smis are 31 bit.
2657 // * A shift of 2 when kSmiTagBits == 0 and kTaggedSizeLog2 == 3, which
2658 // is the case when pointer compression is off, Smis are 32 bit, and
2659 // the Smi was untagged to int32 already.
2660 //
2661 // These shifts are small enough to encode in the load operand.
2662 //
2663 // For out-of-object properties, the encoding is:
2664 //
2665 // field_index = (-1 - array_index) | is_double_bit | smi_tag
2666 // = (-1 - array_index) << (1+kSmiTagBits)
2667 // + is_double_bit << kSmiTagBits
2668 // = -array_index << (1+kSmiTagBits)
2669 // - 1 << (1+kSmiTagBits) + is_double_bit << kSmiTagBits
2670 // = -array_index << (1+kSmiTagBits)
2671 // - 2 << kSmiTagBits + is_double_bit << kSmiTagBits
2672 // = -array_index << (1+kSmiTagBits)
2673 // (is_double_bit - 2) << kSmiTagBits
2674 //
2675 // The value we want is in the property array at offset:
2676 //
2677 // (array_index << kTaggedSizeLog2) + OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray)
2678 //
2679 // [Split shift to match array_index component of field_index]
2680 // = (array_index << (1+kSmiTagBits)) << (kTaggedSizeLog2-1-kSmiTagBits)
2681 // + OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray)
2682 //
2683 // [Substitute in field_index]
2684 // = (-field_index - (is_double_bit - 2) << kSmiTagBits)
2685 // << (kTaggedSizeLog2-1-kSmiTagBits)
2686 // + OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray)
2687 //
2688 // [Fold together the constants]
2689 // = -field_index << (kTaggedSizeLog2-1-kSmiTagBits)
2690 // + OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray)
2691 // - (is_double_bit - 2) << (kTaggedSizeLog2-1))
2692 //
2693 // This allows us to simply negate the field_index register and do a load with
2694 // otherwise constant offset and the same scale factor as for in-object
2695 // properties.
2696
2697 static constexpr int kSmiTagBitsInValue = SmiValuesAre32Bits() ? 0 : 1;
2698 static_assert(kSmiTagBitsInValue == 32 - kSmiValueSize);
2699 if (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
2700 __ SmiUntag(field_index);
2701 }
2702
2703 static constexpr int scale = 1 << (kTaggedSizeLog2 - 1 - kSmiTagBitsInValue);
2704
2705 // Check if field is a mutable double field.
2706 static constexpr int32_t kIsDoubleBitMask = 1 << kSmiTagBitsInValue;
2707 __ TestInt32AndJumpIfAnySet(
2708 field_index, kIsDoubleBitMask,
2709 __ MakeDeferredCode(
2710 [](MaglevAssembler* masm, Register object, Register field_index,
2711 Register result_reg, RegisterSnapshot register_snapshot,
2712 ZoneLabelRef done) {
2713 // The field is a Double field, a.k.a. a mutable HeapNumber.
2714 static constexpr int kIsDoubleBit = 1;
2715
2716 // Check if field is in-object or out-of-object. The is_double bit
2717 // value doesn't matter, since negative values will stay negative.
2718 Label if_outofobject, loaded_field;
2719 __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(field_index, 0, kLessThan,
2720 &if_outofobject);
2721
2722 // The field is located in the {object} itself.
2723 {
2724 // See giant comment above.
2725 if (SmiValuesAre31Bits() && kTaggedSize != kSystemPointerSize) {
2726 // We haven't untagged, so we need to sign extend.
2727 __ SignExtend32To64Bits(field_index, field_index);
2728 }
2729 __ LoadTaggedFieldByIndex(
2730 result_reg, object, field_index, scale,
2731 JSObject::kHeaderSize -
2732 (kIsDoubleBit << (kTaggedSizeLog2 - 1)));
2733 __ Jump(&loaded_field);
2734 }
2735
2736 __ bind(&if_outofobject);
2737 {
2738 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
2739 Register property_array = temps.Acquire();
2740 // Load the property array.
2741 __ LoadTaggedField(
2742 property_array,
2743 FieldMemOperand(object, JSObject::kPropertiesOrHashOffset));
2744
2745 // See giant comment above. No need to sign extend, negate will
2746 // handle it.
2747 __ NegateInt32(field_index);
2748 __ LoadTaggedFieldByIndex(
2749 result_reg, property_array, field_index, scale,
2750 OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray) -
2751 ((2 - kIsDoubleBit) << (kTaggedSizeLog2 - 1)));
2752 __ Jump(&loaded_field);
2753 }
2754
2755 __ bind(&loaded_field);
2756 // We may have transitioned in-place away from double, so check that
2757 // this is a HeapNumber -- otherwise the load is fine and we don't
2758 // need to copy anything anyway.
2759 __ JumpIfSmi(result_reg, *done);
2760 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
2761 Register map = temps.Acquire();
2762 // Hack: The temporary allocated for `map` might alias the result
2763 // register. If it does, use the field_index register as a temporary
2764 // instead (since it's clobbered anyway).
2765 // TODO(leszeks): Extend the result register's lifetime to overlap
2766 // the temporaries, so that this alias isn't possible.
2767 if (map == result_reg) {
2768 DCHECK_NE(map, field_index);
2769 map = field_index;
2770 }
2771 __ LoadMapForCompare(map, result_reg);
2772 __ JumpIfNotRoot(map, RootIndex::kHeapNumberMap, *done);
2773 DoubleRegister double_value = temps.AcquireDouble();
2774 __ LoadHeapNumberValue(double_value, result_reg);
2775 __ AllocateHeapNumber(register_snapshot, result_reg, double_value);
2776 __ Jump(*done);
2777 },
2778 object, field_index, result_reg, register_snapshot(), done));
2779
2780 // The field is a proper Tagged field on {object}. The {field_index} is
2781 // shifted to the left by one in the code below.
2782 {
2783 static constexpr int kIsDoubleBit = 0;
2784
2785 // Check if field is in-object or out-of-object. The is_double bit value
2786 // doesn't matter, since negative values will stay negative.
2787 Label if_outofobject;
2788 __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(field_index, 0, kLessThan, &if_outofobject);
2789
2790 // The field is located in the {object} itself.
2791 {
2792 // See giant comment above.
2793 if (SmiValuesAre31Bits() && kTaggedSize != kSystemPointerSize) {
2794 // We haven't untagged, so we need to sign extend.
2795 __ SignExtend32To64Bits(field_index, field_index);
2796 }
2797 __ LoadTaggedFieldByIndex(
2798 result_reg, object, field_index, scale,
2799 JSObject::kHeaderSize - (kIsDoubleBit << (kTaggedSizeLog2 - 1)));
2800 __ Jump(*done);
2801 }
2802
2803 __ bind(&if_outofobject);
2804 {
2805 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
2806 Register property_array = temps.Acquire();
2807 // Load the property array.
2808 __ LoadTaggedField(
2809 property_array,
2810 FieldMemOperand(object, JSObject::kPropertiesOrHashOffset));
2811
2812 // See giant comment above. No need to sign extend, negate will handle it.
2813 __ NegateInt32(field_index);
2814 __ LoadTaggedFieldByIndex(
2815 result_reg, property_array, field_index, scale,
2816 OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray) -
2817 ((2 - kIsDoubleBit) << (kTaggedSizeLog2 - 1)));
2818 // Fallthrough to `done`.
2819 }
2820 }
2821
2822 __ bind(*done);
2823}

2985 }

2989void LoadSignedIntDataViewElement::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
2990 const ProcessingState& state) {
2991 Register object = ToRegister(object_input());
2992 Register index = ToRegister(index_input());
2993 Register result_reg = ToRegister(result());
2994
2995 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
2996 __ AssertObjectTypeInRange(object,
2997 FIRST_JS_DATA_VIEW_OR_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE,
2998 LAST_JS_DATA_VIEW_OR_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE,
2999 AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
3000 }
3001
3002 int element_size = compiler::ExternalArrayElementSize(type_);
3003
3004 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
3005 Register data_pointer = temps.Acquire();
3006
3007 // We need to make sure we don't clobber is_little_endian_input by writing to
3008 // the result register.
3009 Register reg_with_result = result_reg;
3010 if (type_ != ExternalArrayType::kExternalInt8Array &&
3011 !is_little_endian_constant() &&
3012 result_reg == ToRegister(is_little_endian_input())) {
3013 reg_with_result = data_pointer;
3014 }
3015
3016 // Load data pointer.
3017 __ LoadExternalPointerField(
3018 data_pointer, FieldMemOperand(object, JSDataView::kDataPointerOffset));
3019 MemOperand element_address = __ DataViewElementOperand(data_pointer, index);
3020 __ LoadSignedField(reg_with_result, element_address, element_size);
3021
3022 // We ignore little endian argument if type is a byte size.
3023 if (type_ != ExternalArrayType::kExternalInt8Array) {
3024 if (is_little_endian_constant()) {
3025 if (!V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN_BOOL &&
3026 !FromConstantToBool(masm, is_little_endian_input().node())) {
3027 DCHECK_EQ(reg_with_result, result_reg);
3028 __ ReverseByteOrder(result_reg, element_size);
3029 }
3030 } else {
3031 ZoneLabelRef keep_byte_order(masm), reverse_byte_order(masm);
3032 DCHECK_NE(reg_with_result, ToRegister(is_little_endian_input()));
3033 __ ToBoolean(
3034 ToRegister(is_little_endian_input()), CheckType::kCheckHeapObject,
3035 V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN_BOOL ? reverse_byte_order : keep_byte_order,
3036 V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN_BOOL ? keep_byte_order : reverse_byte_order,
3037 false);
3038 __ bind(*reverse_byte_order);
3039 __ ReverseByteOrder(reg_with_result, element_size);
3040 __ bind(*keep_byte_order);
3041 if (reg_with_result != result_reg) {
3042 __ Move(result_reg, reg_with_result);
3043 }
3044 }
3045 }
3046}

3053 } else {
3054 UseRegister(value_input());
3055 }
3056 if (is_little_endian_constant() ||
3057 type_ == ExternalArrayType::kExternalInt8Array) {
3058 UseAny(is_little_endian_input());
3059 } else {
3060 UseRegister(is_little_endian_input());
3061 }
3062 set_temporaries_needed(1);

3064void StoreSignedIntDataViewElement::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
3065 const ProcessingState& state) {
3066 Register object = ToRegister(object_input());
3067 Register index = ToRegister(index_input());
3068 Register value = ToRegister(value_input());
3069
3070 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
3071 __ AssertObjectTypeInRange(object,
3072 FIRST_JS_DATA_VIEW_OR_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE,
3073 LAST_JS_DATA_VIEW_OR_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE,
3074 AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
3075 }
3076
3077 int element_size = compiler::ExternalArrayElementSize(type_);
3078
3079 // We ignore little endian argument if type is a byte size.
3080 if (element_size > 1) {
3081 if (is_little_endian_constant()) {
3082 if (!V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN_BOOL &&
3083 !FromConstantToBool(masm, is_little_endian_input().node())) {
3084 __ ReverseByteOrder(value, element_size);
3085 }
3086 } else {
3087 ZoneLabelRef keep_byte_order(masm), reverse_byte_order(masm);
3088 __ ToBoolean(
3089 ToRegister(is_little_endian_input()), CheckType::kCheckHeapObject,
3090 V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN_BOOL ? reverse_byte_order : keep_byte_order,
3091 V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN_BOOL ? keep_byte_order : reverse_byte_order,
3092 false);
3093 __ bind(*reverse_byte_order);
3094 __ ReverseByteOrder(value, element_size);
3095 __ bind(*keep_byte_order);
3096 }
3097 }

3099 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
3100 Register data_pointer = temps.Acquire();
3101 __ LoadExternalPointerField(
3102 data_pointer, FieldMemOperand(object, JSDataView::kDataPointerOffset));
3103 MemOperand element_address = __ DataViewElementOperand(data_pointer, index);
3104 __ StoreField(element_address, value, element_size);

3109 UseRegister(index_input());

3118void LoadDoubleDataViewElement::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
3119 const ProcessingState& state) {
3120 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
3121 Register object = ToRegister(object_input());
3122 Register index = ToRegister(index_input());
3123 DoubleRegister result_reg = ToDoubleRegister(result());
3124 Register data_pointer = temps.Acquire();
3125
3126 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
3127 __ AssertObjectTypeInRange(object,
3128 FIRST_JS_DATA_VIEW_OR_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE,
3129 LAST_JS_DATA_VIEW_OR_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE,
3130 AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
3131 }
3132
3133 // Load data pointer.
3134 __ LoadExternalPointerField(
3135 data_pointer, FieldMemOperand(object, JSDataView::kDataPointerOffset));
3136
3137 if (is_little_endian_constant()) {
3138 if (!V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN_BOOL &&
3139 FromConstantToBool(masm, is_little_endian_input().node())) {
3140 __ LoadUnalignedFloat64(result_reg, data_pointer, index);
3141 } else {
3142 __ LoadUnalignedFloat64AndReverseByteOrder(result_reg, data_pointer,
3143 index);
3144 }
3145 } else {
3146 Label done;
3147 ZoneLabelRef keep_byte_order(masm), reverse_byte_order(masm);
3148 // TODO(leszeks): We're likely to be calling this on an existing boolean --
3149 // maybe that's a case we should fast-path here and re-use that boolean
3150 // value?
3151 __ ToBoolean(
3152 ToRegister(is_little_endian_input()), CheckType::kCheckHeapObject,
3153 V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN_BOOL ? reverse_byte_order : keep_byte_order,
3154 V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN_BOOL ? keep_byte_order : reverse_byte_order, true);
3155 __ bind(*keep_byte_order);
3156 __ LoadUnalignedFloat64(result_reg, data_pointer, index);
3157 __ Jump(&done);
3158 // We should swap the bytes if big endian.
3159 __ bind(*reverse_byte_order);
3160 __ LoadUnalignedFloat64AndReverseByteOrder(result_reg, data_pointer, index);
3161 __ bind(&done);
3162 }

3165void StoreDoubleDataViewElement::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
3166 UseRegister(object_input());
3167 UseRegister(index_input());
3168 UseRegister(value_input());
3169 if (is_little_endian_constant()) {
3170 UseAny(is_little_endian_input());
3171 } else {
3172 UseRegister(is_little_endian_input());
3173 }
3174 set_temporaries_needed(1);
3175}
3176void StoreDoubleDataViewElement::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
3177 const ProcessingState& state) {
3178 Register object = ToRegister(object_input());
3179 Register index = ToRegister(index_input());
3180 DoubleRegister value = ToDoubleRegister(value_input());
3181 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
3182 Register data_pointer = temps.Acquire();
3183
3184 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
3185 __ AssertObjectTypeInRange(object,
3186 FIRST_JS_DATA_VIEW_OR_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE,
3187 LAST_JS_DATA_VIEW_OR_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE,
3188 AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
3189 }
3190
3191 // Load data pointer.
3192 __ LoadExternalPointerField(
3193 data_pointer, FieldMemOperand(object, JSDataView::kDataPointerOffset));
3194
3195 if (is_little_endian_constant()) {
3196 if (!V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN_BOOL &&
3197 FromConstantToBool(masm, is_little_endian_input().node())) {
3198 __ StoreUnalignedFloat64(data_pointer, index, value);
3199 } else {
3200 __ ReverseByteOrderAndStoreUnalignedFloat64(data_pointer, index, value);
3201 }
3202 } else {
3203 Label done;
3204 ZoneLabelRef keep_byte_order(masm), reverse_byte_order(masm);
3205 // TODO(leszeks): We're likely to be calling this on an existing boolean --
3206 // maybe that's a case we should fast-path here and re-use that boolean
3207 // value?
3208 __ ToBoolean(
3209 ToRegister(is_little_endian_input()), CheckType::kCheckHeapObject,
3210 V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN_BOOL ? reverse_byte_order : keep_byte_order,
3211 V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN_BOOL ? keep_byte_order : reverse_byte_order, true);
3212 __ bind(*keep_byte_order);
3213 __ StoreUnalignedFloat64(data_pointer, index, value);
3214 __ Jump(&done);
3215 // We should swap the bytes if big endian.
3216 __ bind(*reverse_byte_order);
3217 __ ReverseByteOrderAndStoreUnalignedFloat64(data_pointer, index, value);
3218 __ bind(&done);
3219 }
3220}

3336void CheckValueEqualsString::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
3337 using D = CallInterfaceDescriptorFor<Builtin::kStringEqual>::type;
3338 UseFixed(target_input(), D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kLeft));
3339 RequireSpecificTemporary(D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kLength));
3340}
3341void CheckValueEqualsString::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
3342 const ProcessingState& state) {
3343 using D = CallInterfaceDescriptorFor<Builtin::kStringEqual>::type;
3344
3345 ZoneLabelRef end(masm);
3346 DCHECK_EQ(D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kLeft), ToRegister(target_input()));
3347 Register target = D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kLeft);
3348 // Maybe the string is internalized already, do a fast reference check first.
3349 __ CompareTaggedAndJumpIf(target, value().object(), kEqual, *end,
3350 Label::kNear);
3351
3352 __ EmitEagerDeoptIfSmi(this, target, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongValue);
3353 __ JumpIfString(
3354 target,
3355 __ MakeDeferredCode(
3356 [](MaglevAssembler* masm, CheckValueEqualsString* node,
3357 ZoneLabelRef end) {
3358 Register target = D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kLeft);
3359 Register string_length = D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kLength);
3360 __ StringLength(string_length, target);
3361 Label* fail = __ GetDeoptLabel(node, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongValue);
3362 __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(string_length, node->value().length(),
3363 kNotEqual, fail);
3364 RegisterSnapshot snapshot = node->register_snapshot();
3365 {
3366 SaveRegisterStateForCall save_register_state(masm, snapshot);
3367 __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kStringEqual>(
3368 node->target_input(), // left
3369 node->value().object(), // right
3370 string_length // length
3371 );
3372 save_register_state.DefineSafepoint();
3373 // Compare before restoring registers, so that the deopt below has
3374 // the correct register set.
3375 __ CompareRoot(kReturnRegister0, RootIndex::kTrueValue);
3376 }
3377 __ EmitEagerDeoptIf(kNotEqual, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongValue, node);
3378 __ Jump(*end);
3379 },
3380 this, end));
3381
3382 __ EmitEagerDeopt(this, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongValue);
3383
3384 __ bind(*end);
3385}

3456void CheckCacheIndicesNotCleared::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
3457 const ProcessingState& state) {
3458 Register indices = ToRegister(indices_input());
3459 Register length = ToRegister(length_input());
3460 __ AssertNotSmi(indices);
3461
3462 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
3463 __ AssertObjectType(indices, FIXED_ARRAY_TYPE,
3464 AbortReason::kOperandIsNotAFixedArray);
3465 }
3466 Label done;
3467 // If the cache length is zero, we don't have any indices, so we know this is
3468 // ok even though the indices are the empty array.
3469 __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(length, 0, kEqual, &done);
3470 // Otherwise, an empty array with non-zero required length is not valid.
3471 __ JumpIfRoot(indices, RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray,
3472 __ GetDeoptLabel(this, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongEnumIndices));
3473 __ bind(&done);

3487 __ ZeroExtendWord(index, index);
3488#endif
3489 __ AssertZeroExtended(index);
