3507 return WriteBarrierDescriptor::GetStackParameterCount();
3508}
3509
3510void StoreScriptContextSlotWithWriteBarrier::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
3511 UseFixed(context_input(), WriteBarrierDescriptor::ObjectRegister());
3512 UseRegister(new_value_input());
3513 set_temporaries_needed(2);
3514 set_double_temporaries_needed(1);
3515}
3516
3517void StoreScriptContextSlotWithWriteBarrier::GenerateCode(
3518 MaglevAssembler* masm, const ProcessingState& state) {
3519 __ RecordComment("StoreScriptContextSlotWithWriteBarrier");
3520 ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
3521 ZoneLabelRef do_normal_store(masm);
3522
3523 // TODO(leszeks): Consider making this an arbitrary register and push/popping
3524 // in the deferred path.
3525 Register context = WriteBarrierDescriptor::ObjectRegister();
3526 Register new_value = ToRegister(new_value_input());
3527 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
3528 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3529 Register old_value = temps.Acquire();
3530
3531 __ AssertObjectType(context, SCRIPT_CONTEXT_TYPE,
3532 AbortReason::kUnexpectedInstanceType);
3533
3534 __ LoadTaggedField(old_value, context, offset());
3535 __ CompareTaggedAndJumpIf(old_value, new_value, kEqual, *done);
3536
3537 // Load property.
3538 // TODO(victorgomes): Should we hoist the side_table?
3539 __ LoadTaggedField(
3540 scratch, context,
3541 Context::OffsetOfElementAt(Context::CONTEXT_SIDE_TABLE_PROPERTY_INDEX));
3542 __ LoadTaggedField(scratch, scratch,
3543 FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(
3544 index() - Context::MIN_CONTEXT_EXTENDED_SLOTS));
3545
3546 __ CompareTaggedAndJumpIf(
3547 scratch, ContextSidePropertyCell::Other(), kNotEqual,
3548 __ MakeDeferredCode(
3549 [](MaglevAssembler* masm, Register context, Register old_value,
3550 Register new_value, Register property,
3551 StoreScriptContextSlotWithWriteBarrier* node, ZoneLabelRef done,
3552 ZoneLabelRef do_normal_store) {
3553 Label check_smi, check_mutable_int32, mutable_heap_number;
3554 __ CompareRootAndEmitEagerDeoptIf(
3555 property, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue, kEqual,
3556 DeoptimizeReason::kWrongValue, node);
3557 __ JumpIfSmi(property, &check_smi);
3558 __ AssertObjectType(property, CONTEXT_SIDE_PROPERTY_CELL_TYPE,
3559 AbortReason::kUnexpectedInstanceType);
3560 __ LoadTaggedField(
3561 property, property,
3562 ContextSidePropertyCell::kPropertyDetailsRawOffset);
3563 __ bind(&check_smi);
3564
3565 // Check for const case.
3566 __ CompareTaggedAndJumpIf(
3567 property, ContextSidePropertyCell::Const(), kEqual,
3568 __ GetDeoptLabel(node, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongValue));
3569
3570 if (v8_flags.script_context_mutable_heap_number) {
3571 // Check for smi case
3572 __ CompareTaggedAndJumpIf(property,
3573 ContextSidePropertyCell::SmiMarker(),
3574 kNotEqual, &check_mutable_int32);
3575 __ EmitEagerDeoptIfNotSmi(node, new_value,
3576 DeoptimizeReason::kWrongValue);
3577 __ Jump(*do_normal_store);
3578
3579 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
3580 DoubleRegister double_scratch = temps.AcquireDouble();
3581
3582 // Check mutable int32 case.
3583 __ bind(&check_mutable_int32);
3584 if (v8_flags.script_context_mutable_heap_int32) {
3585 __ CompareTaggedAndJumpIf(
3586 property, ContextSidePropertyCell::MutableInt32(),
3587 kNotEqual, &mutable_heap_number);
3588 {
3589 Label new_value_is_not_smi;
3590 Register new_value_int32 = property;
3591 __ JumpIfNotSmi(new_value, &new_value_is_not_smi);
3592 __ SmiUntag(new_value_int32, new_value);
3593 __ StoreHeapInt32Value(new_value_int32, old_value);
3594 __ Jump(*done);
3595
3596 __ bind(&new_value_is_not_smi);
3597 __ CompareMapWithRoot(new_value, RootIndex::kHeapNumberMap,
3598 property);
3599 __ EmitEagerDeoptIf(kNotEqual, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongValue,
3600 node);
3601
3602 __ LoadHeapNumberValue(double_scratch, new_value);
3603 __ TryTruncateDoubleToInt32(
3604 new_value_int32, double_scratch,
3605 __ GetDeoptLabel(node, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongValue));
3606 __ StoreHeapInt32Value(new_value_int32, old_value);
3607 __ Jump(*done);
3608 }
3609 }
3610
3611 // Check mutable heap number case.
3612 __ bind(&mutable_heap_number);
3613 {
3614 Label new_value_is_not_smi;
3615 Register new_value_int32 = property;
3616 __ JumpIfNotSmi(new_value, &new_value_is_not_smi);
3617 __ SmiUntag(new_value_int32, new_value);
3618 __ Int32ToDouble(double_scratch, new_value_int32);
3619 __ StoreHeapNumberValue(double_scratch, old_value);
3620 __ Jump(*done);
3621
3622 __ bind(&new_value_is_not_smi);
3623 __ CompareMapWithRoot(new_value, RootIndex::kHeapNumberMap,
3624 property);
3625 __ EmitEagerDeoptIf(kNotEqual, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongValue,
3626 node);
3627 __ LoadHeapNumberValue(double_scratch, new_value);
3628 __ StoreHeapNumberValue(double_scratch, old_value);
3629 __ Jump(*done);
3630 }
3631 } else {
3632 __ Jump(*do_normal_store);
3633 }
3634 },
3635 context, old_value, new_value, scratch, this, done, do_normal_store));
3636
3637 __ bind(*do_normal_store);
3638 __ StoreTaggedFieldWithWriteBarrier(
3639 context, offset(), new_value, register_snapshot(),
3640 new_value_input().node()->decompresses_tagged_result()
3641 ? MaglevAssembler::kValueIsDecompressed
3642 : MaglevAssembler::kValueIsCompressed,
3643 MaglevAssembler::kValueCanBeSmi);
3644
3645 __ bind(*done);
3646}

3663void CheckStringOrStringWrapper::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
3664 UseRegister(receiver_input());
3665 set_temporaries_needed(1);
3666}
3667
3668void CheckStringOrStringWrapper::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
3669 const ProcessingState& state) {
3670 Register object = ToRegister(receiver_input());
3671
3672 if (check_type() == CheckType::kOmitHeapObjectCheck) {
3673 __ AssertNotSmi(object);
3674 } else {
3675 __ EmitEagerDeoptIfSmi(this, object,
3676 DeoptimizeReason::kNotAStringOrStringWrapper);
3677 }
3678
3679 auto deopt =
3680 __ GetDeoptLabel(this, DeoptimizeReason::kNotAStringOrStringWrapper);
3681 Label done;
3682
3683 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
3684 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3685
3686 __ JumpIfString(object, &done);
3687 __ JumpIfNotObjectType(object, InstanceType::JS_PRIMITIVE_WRAPPER_TYPE,
3688 deopt);
3689 __ LoadMap(scratch, object);
3690 __ LoadBitField<Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits>(
3691 scratch, FieldMemOperand(scratch, Map::kBitField2Offset));
3692 static_assert(FAST_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS + 1 ==
3693 SLOW_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS);
3694 __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(scratch, FAST_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS, kLessThan,
3695 deopt);
3696 __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(scratch, SLOW_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS, kGreaterThan,
3697 deopt);
3698 __ Jump(&done);
3699 __ bind(&done);
3700}

3741int ConvertReceiver::MaxCallStackArgs() const {
3742 using D = CallInterfaceDescriptorFor<Builtin::kToObject>::type;
3743 return D::GetStackParameterCount();
3744}
3745void ConvertReceiver::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
3746 using D = CallInterfaceDescriptorFor<Builtin::kToObject>::type;
3747 static_assert(D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kInput) == kReturnRegister0);
3748 UseFixed(receiver_input(), D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kInput));
3749 DefineAsFixed(this, kReturnRegister0);
3750}
3751void ConvertReceiver::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
3752 const ProcessingState& state) {
3753 Label convert_to_object, done;
3754 Register receiver = ToRegister(receiver_input());
3755 __ JumpIfSmi(
3756 receiver, &convert_to_object,
3757 v8_flags.debug_code ? Label::Distance::kFar : Label::Distance::kNear);
3758
3759 // If {receiver} is not primitive, no need to move it to {result}, since
3760 // they share the same register.
3761 DCHECK_EQ(receiver, ToRegister(result()));
3762 __ JumpIfJSAnyIsNotPrimitive(receiver, &done);
3763
3764 compiler::JSHeapBroker* broker = masm->compilation_info()->broker();
3765 if (mode_ != ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined) {
3766 Label convert_global_proxy;
3767 __ JumpIfRoot(receiver, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue, &convert_global_proxy,
3768 Label::Distance::kNear);
3769 __ JumpIfNotRoot(
3770 receiver, RootIndex::kNullValue, &convert_to_object,
3771 v8_flags.debug_code ? Label::Distance::kFar : Label::Distance::kNear);
3772 __ bind(&convert_global_proxy);
3773 // Patch receiver to global proxy.
3774 __ Move(ToRegister(result()),
3775 native_context_.global_proxy_object(broker).object());
3776 __ Jump(&done);
3777 }
3778
3779 __ bind(&convert_to_object);
3780 __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kToObject>(native_context_.object(),
3781 receiver_input());
3782 __ bind(&done);
3783}
3784
3785int CheckDerivedConstructResult::MaxCallStackArgs() const { return 0; }
3786void CheckDerivedConstructResult::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
3787 UseRegister(construct_result_input());
3788 DefineSameAsFirst(this);
3789}
3790void CheckDerivedConstructResult::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
3791 const ProcessingState& state) {
3792 Register construct_result = ToRegister(construct_result_input());
3793
3794 DCHECK_EQ(construct_result, ToRegister(result()));
3795
3796 // If the result is an object (in the ECMA sense), we should get rid
3797 // of the receiver and use the result; see ECMA-262 section 13.2.2-7
3798 // on page 74.
3799 Label done, do_throw;
3800
3801 __ CompareRoot(construct_result, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
3802 __ Assert(kNotEqual, AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
3803
3804 // If the result is a smi, it is *not* an object in the ECMA sense.
3805 __ JumpIfSmi(construct_result, &do_throw, Label::Distance::kNear);
3806
3807 // Check if the type of the result is not an object in the ECMA sense.
3808 __ JumpIfJSAnyIsNotPrimitive(construct_result, &done, Label::Distance::kNear);
3809
3810 // Throw away the result of the constructor invocation and use the
3811 // implicit receiver as the result.
3812 __ bind(&do_throw);
3813 __ Jump(__ MakeDeferredCode(
3814 [](MaglevAssembler* masm, CheckDerivedConstructResult* node) {
3815 __ Move(kContextRegister, masm->native_context().object());
3816 __ CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowConstructorReturnedNonObject);
3817 masm->DefineExceptionHandlerAndLazyDeoptPoint(node);
3818 __ Abort(AbortReason::kUnexpectedReturnFromThrow);
3819 },
3820 this));
3821
3822 __ bind(&done);
3823}
3824
3825int CheckConstructResult::MaxCallStackArgs() const { return 0; }
3826void CheckConstructResult::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
3827 UseRegister(construct_result_input());
3828 UseRegister(implicit_receiver_input());
3829 DefineSameAsFirst(this);
3830}
3831void CheckConstructResult::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
3832 const ProcessingState& state) {
3833 Register construct_result = ToRegister(construct_result_input());
3834 Register result_reg = ToRegister(result());
3835
3836 DCHECK_EQ(construct_result, result_reg);
3837
3838 // If the result is an object (in the ECMA sense), we should get rid
3839 // of the receiver and use the result; see ECMA-262 section 13.2.2-7
3840 // on page 74.
3841 Label done, use_receiver;
3842
3843 // If the result is undefined, we'll use the implicit receiver.
3844 __ JumpIfRoot(construct_result, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue, &use_receiver,
3845 Label::Distance::kNear);
3846
3847 // If the result is a smi, it is *not* an object in the ECMA sense.
3848 __ JumpIfSmi(construct_result, &use_receiver, Label::Distance::kNear);
3849
3850 // Check if the type of the result is not an object in the ECMA sense.
3851 __ JumpIfJSAnyIsNotPrimitive(construct_result, &done, Label::Distance::kNear);
3852
3853 // Throw away the result of the constructor invocation and use the
3854 // implicit receiver as the result.
3855 __ bind(&use_receiver);
3856 Register implicit_receiver = ToRegister(implicit_receiver_input());
3857 __ Move(result_reg, implicit_receiver);
3858
3859 __ bind(&done);
3860}

4074int HasInPrototypeChain::MaxCallStackArgs() const {
4075 DCHECK_EQ(2, Runtime::FunctionForId(Runtime::kHasInPrototypeChain)->nargs);
4076 return 2;
4077}
4078void HasInPrototypeChain::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
4079 UseRegister(object());
4080 DefineAsRegister(this);
4081 set_temporaries_needed(2);
4082}
4083void HasInPrototypeChain::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
4084 const ProcessingState& state) {
4085 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
4086 Register object_reg = ToRegister(object());
4087 Register result_reg = ToRegister(result());
4088
4089 Label return_false, return_true;
4090 ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
4091
4092 __ JumpIfSmi(object_reg, &return_false,
4093 v8_flags.debug_code ? Label::kFar : Label::kNear);
4094
4095 // Loop through the prototype chain looking for the {prototype}.
4096 Register map = temps.Acquire();
4097 __ LoadMap(map, object_reg);
4098 Label loop;
4099 {
4100 __ bind(&loop);
4101 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4102 // Check if we can determine the prototype directly from the {object_map}.
4103 ZoneLabelRef if_objectisdirect(masm);
4104 Register instance_type = scratch;
4105 Condition jump_cond = __ CompareInstanceTypeRange(
4106 map, instance_type, FIRST_TYPE, LAST_SPECIAL_RECEIVER_TYPE);
4107 __ JumpToDeferredIf(
4108 jump_cond,
4109 [](MaglevAssembler* masm, RegisterSnapshot snapshot,
4110 Register object_reg, Register map, Register instance_type,
4111 Register result_reg, HasInPrototypeChain* node,
4112 ZoneLabelRef if_objectisdirect, ZoneLabelRef done) {
4113 Label return_runtime;
4114 // The {object_map} is a special receiver map or a primitive map,
4115 // check if we need to use the if_objectisspecial path in the runtime.
4116 __ JumpIfEqual(instance_type, JS_PROXY_TYPE, &return_runtime);
4117
4118 int mask = Map::Bits1::HasNamedInterceptorBit::kMask |
4119 Map::Bits1::IsAccessCheckNeededBit::kMask;
4120 __ TestUint8AndJumpIfAllClear(
4121 FieldMemOperand(map, Map::kBitFieldOffset), mask,
4122 *if_objectisdirect);
4123
4124 __ bind(&return_runtime);
4125 {
4126 snapshot.live_registers.clear(result_reg);
4127 SaveRegisterStateForCall save_register_state(masm, snapshot);
4128 __ Push(object_reg, node->prototype().object());
4129 __ Move(kContextRegister, masm->native_context().object());
4130 __ CallRuntime(Runtime::kHasInPrototypeChain, 2);
4131 masm->DefineExceptionHandlerPoint(node);
4132 save_register_state.DefineSafepointWithLazyDeopt(
4133 node->lazy_deopt_info());
4134 __ Move(result_reg, kReturnRegister0);
4135 }
4136 __ Jump(*done);
4137 },
4138 register_snapshot(), object_reg, map, instance_type, result_reg, this,
4139 if_objectisdirect, done);
4140 instance_type = Register::no_reg();
4141
4142 __ bind(*if_objectisdirect);
4143 // Check the current {object} prototype.
4144 Register object_prototype = scratch;
4145 __ LoadTaggedField(object_prototype, map, Map::kPrototypeOffset);
4146 __ JumpIfRoot(object_prototype, RootIndex::kNullValue, &return_false,
4147 v8_flags.debug_code ? Label::kFar : Label::kNear);
4148 __ CompareTaggedAndJumpIf(object_prototype, prototype().object(), kEqual,
4149 &return_true, Label::kNear);
4150
4151 // Continue with the prototype.
4152 __ AssertNotSmi(object_prototype);
4153 __ LoadMap(map, object_prototype);
4154 __ Jump(&loop);
4155 }
4156
4157 __ bind(&return_true);
4158 __ LoadRoot(result_reg, RootIndex::kTrueValue);
4159 __ Jump(*done, Label::kNear);
4160
4161 __ bind(&return_false);
4162 __ LoadRoot(result_reg, RootIndex::kFalseValue);
4163 __ bind(*done);
4164}

4187void LogicalNot::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
4188 const ProcessingState& state) {
4189 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
4190 // LogicalNot expects either TrueValue or FalseValue.
4191 Label next;
4192 __ JumpIf(__ IsRootConstant(value(), RootIndex::kFalseValue), &next);
4193 __ JumpIf(__ IsRootConstant(value(), RootIndex::kTrueValue), &next);
4194 __ Abort(AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
4195 __ bind(&next);
4196 }
4197
4198 Label return_false, done;
4199 __ JumpIf(__ IsRootConstant(value(), RootIndex::kTrueValue), &return_false);
4200 __ LoadRoot(ToRegister(result()), RootIndex::kTrueValue);
4201 __ Jump(&done);
4202
4203 __ bind(&return_false);
4204 __ LoadRoot(ToRegister(result()), RootIndex::kFalseValue);
4205
4206 __ bind(&done);
4207}

4302void UpdateJSArrayLength::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
4303 UseRegister(length_input());
4304 UseRegister(object_input());
4305 UseAndClobberRegister(index_input());
4306 DefineSameAsFirst(this);
4307}
4308
4309void UpdateJSArrayLength::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
4310 const ProcessingState& state) {
4311 Register length = ToRegister(length_input());
4312 Register object = ToRegister(object_input());
4313 Register index = ToRegister(index_input());
4314 DCHECK_EQ(length, ToRegister(result()));
4315
4316 Label done, tag_length;
4317 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
4318 __ AssertObjectType(object, JS_ARRAY_TYPE, AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
4319 static_assert(Internals::IsValidSmi(FixedArray::kMaxLength),
4320 "MaxLength not a Smi");
4321 __ CompareInt32AndAssert(index, FixedArray::kMaxLength, kUnsignedLessThan,
4322 AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
4323 }
4324 __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(index, length, kUnsignedLessThan, &tag_length,
4325 Label::kNear);
4326 __ IncrementInt32(index); // This cannot overflow.
4327 __ SmiTag(length, index);
4328 __ StoreTaggedSignedField(object, JSArray::kLengthOffset, length);
4329 __ Jump(&done, Label::kNear);
4330 __ bind(&tag_length);
4331 __ SmiTag(length);
4332 __ bind(&done);
4333}

4351void MaybeGrowFastElements::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
4352 UseRegister(elements_input());
4353 UseRegister(object_input());
4354 UseRegister(index_input());
4355 UseRegister(elements_length_input());
4356 if (IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(elements_kind())) {
4357 set_temporaries_needed(1);
4358 }
4359 DefineSameAsFirst(this);
4360}
4361void MaybeGrowFastElements::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
4362 const ProcessingState& state) {
4363 Register elements = ToRegister(elements_input());
4364 Register object = ToRegister(object_input());
4365 Register index = ToRegister(index_input());
4366 Register elements_length = ToRegister(elements_length_input());
4367 DCHECK_EQ(elements, ToRegister(result()));
4368
4369 ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
4370
4371 __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(
4372 index, elements_length, kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual,
4373 __ MakeDeferredCode(
4374 [](MaglevAssembler* masm, ZoneLabelRef done, Register object,
4375 Register index, Register result_reg, MaybeGrowFastElements* node) {
4376 {
4377 RegisterSnapshot snapshot = node->register_snapshot();
4378 snapshot.live_registers.clear(result_reg);
4379 snapshot.live_tagged_registers.clear(result_reg);
4380 SaveRegisterStateForCall save_register_state(masm, snapshot);
4381 using D = GrowArrayElementsDescriptor;
4382 if (index == D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kObject)) {
4383 // That implies that the first parameter move will clobber the
4384 // index value. So we use the result register as temporary.
4385 // TODO(leszeks): Use parallel moves to resolve cases like this.
4386 __ SmiTag(result_reg, index);
4387 index = result_reg;
4388 } else {
4389 __ SmiTag(index);
4390 }
4391 if (IsDoubleElementsKind(node->elements_kind())) {
4392 __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kGrowFastDoubleElements>(object, index);
4393 } else {
4394 __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kGrowFastSmiOrObjectElements>(object,
4395 index);
4396 }
4397 save_register_state.DefineSafepoint();
4398 __ Move(result_reg, kReturnRegister0);
4399 }
4400 __ EmitEagerDeoptIfSmi(node, result_reg,
4401 DeoptimizeReason::kCouldNotGrowElements);
4402 __ Jump(*done);
4403 },
4404 done, object, index, elements, this));
4405
4406 __ bind(*done);
4407}
4408
4409void ExtendPropertiesBackingStore::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
4410 UseRegister(property_array_input());
4411 UseRegister(object_input());
4412 DefineAsRegister(this);
4413 set_temporaries_needed(2);
4414}
4415
4416void ExtendPropertiesBackingStore::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
4417 const ProcessingState& state) {
4418 Register object = ToRegister(object_input());
4419 Register old_property_array = ToRegister(property_array_input());
4420 Register result_reg = ToRegister(result());
4421 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
4422 Register new_property_array =
4423 result_reg == object || result_reg == old_property_array ? temps.Acquire()
4424 : result_reg;
4425 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4426 DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, old_property_array, new_property_array, scratch));
4427
4428 int new_length = old_length_ + JSObject::kFieldsAdded;
4429
4430 // Allocate new PropertyArray.
4431 {
4432 RegisterSnapshot snapshot = register_snapshot();
4433 // old_property_array needs to be live, since we'll read data from it.
4434 // Object needs to be live, since we write the new property array into it.
4435 snapshot.live_registers.set(object);
4436 snapshot.live_registers.set(old_property_array);
4437 snapshot.live_tagged_registers.set(object);
4438 snapshot.live_tagged_registers.set(old_property_array);
4439
4440 Register size_in_bytes = scratch;
4441 __ Move(size_in_bytes, PropertyArray::SizeFor(new_length));
4442 __ Allocate(snapshot, new_property_array, size_in_bytes,
4443 AllocationType::kYoung);
4444 __ SetMapAsRoot(new_property_array, RootIndex::kPropertyArrayMap);
4445 }
4446
4447 // Copy existing properties over.
4448 {
4449 RegisterSnapshot snapshot = register_snapshot();
4450 snapshot.live_registers.set(object);
4451 snapshot.live_registers.set(old_property_array);
4452 snapshot.live_registers.set(new_property_array);
4453 snapshot.live_tagged_registers.set(object);
4454 snapshot.live_tagged_registers.set(old_property_array);
4455 snapshot.live_tagged_registers.set(new_property_array);
4456
4457 for (int i = 0; i < old_length_; ++i) {
4458 __ LoadTaggedFieldWithoutDecompressing(
4459 scratch, old_property_array, PropertyArray::OffsetOfElementAt(i));
4460
4461 __ StoreTaggedFieldWithWriteBarrier(
4462 new_property_array, PropertyArray::OffsetOfElementAt(i), scratch,
4463 snapshot, MaglevAssembler::kValueIsCompressed,
4464 MaglevAssembler::kValueCanBeSmi);
4465 }
4466 }
4467
4468 // Initialize new properties to undefined.
4469 __ LoadRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
4470 for (int i = 0; i < JSObject::kFieldsAdded; ++i) {
4471 __ StoreTaggedFieldNoWriteBarrier(
4472 new_property_array, PropertyArray::OffsetOfElementAt(old_length_ + i),
4473 scratch);
4474 }
4475
4476 // Read the hash.
4477 if (old_length_ == 0) {
4478 // The object might still have a hash, stored in properties_or_hash. If
4479 // properties_or_hash is a SMI, then it's the hash. It can also be an empty
4480 // PropertyArray.
4481 __ LoadTaggedField(scratch, object, JSObject::kPropertiesOrHashOffset);
4482
4483 Label done;
4484 __ JumpIfSmi(scratch, &done);
4485
4486 __ Move(scratch, PropertyArray::kNoHashSentinel);
4487
4488 __ bind(&done);
4489 __ SmiUntag(scratch);
4490 __ ShiftLeft(scratch, PropertyArray::HashField::kShift);
4491 } else {
4492 __ LoadTaggedField(scratch, old_property_array,
4493 PropertyArray::kLengthAndHashOffset);
4494 __ SmiUntag(scratch);
4495 __ AndInt32(scratch, PropertyArray::HashField::kMask);
4496 }
4497
4498 // Add the new length and write the length-and-hash field.
4499 static_assert(PropertyArray::LengthField::kShift == 0);
4500 __ OrInt32(scratch, new_length);
4501
4502 __ UncheckedSmiTagInt32(scratch, scratch);
4503 __ StoreTaggedFieldNoWriteBarrier(
4504 new_property_array, PropertyArray::kLengthAndHashOffset, scratch);
4505
4506 {
4507 RegisterSnapshot snapshot = register_snapshot();
4508 // new_property_array needs to be live since we'll return it.
4509 snapshot.live_registers.set(new_property_array);
4510 snapshot.live_tagged_registers.set(new_property_array);
4511
4512 __ StoreTaggedFieldWithWriteBarrier(
4513 object, JSObject::kPropertiesOrHashOffset, new_property_array, snapshot,
4514 MaglevAssembler::kValueIsDecompressed,
4515 MaglevAssembler::kValueCannotBeSmi);
4516 }
4517 if (result_reg != new_property_array) {
4518 __ Move(result_reg, new_property_array);
4519 }
4520}

4599void GeneratorRestoreRegister::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
4600 UseRegister(array_input());
4601 UseRegister(stale_input());
4602 DefineAsRegister(this);
4603 set_temporaries_needed(1);
4604}
4605void GeneratorRestoreRegister::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
4606 const ProcessingState& state) {
4607 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
4608 Register temp = temps.Acquire();
4609 Register array = ToRegister(array_input());
4610 Register stale = ToRegister(stale_input());
4611 Register result_reg = ToRegister(result());
4612
4613 // The input and the output can alias, if that happens we use a temporary
4614 // register and a move at the end.
4615 Register value = (array == result_reg ? temp : result_reg);
4616
4617 // Loads the current value in the generator register file.
4618 __ LoadTaggedField(value, array, FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(index()));
4619
4620 // And trashs it with StaleRegisterConstant.
4621 DCHECK(stale_input().node()->Is<RootConstant>());
4622 __ StoreTaggedFieldNoWriteBarrier(
4623 array, FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(index()), stale);
4624
4625 if (value != result_reg) {
4626 __ Move(result_reg, value);
4627 }
4628}

4630int GeneratorStore::MaxCallStackArgs() const {
4631 return WriteBarrierDescriptor::GetStackParameterCount();
4632}
4633void GeneratorStore::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
4634 UseAny(context_input());
4635 UseRegister(generator_input());
4636 for (int i = 0; i < num_parameters_and_registers(); i++) {
4637 UseAny(parameters_and_registers(i));
4638 }
4639 RequireSpecificTemporary(WriteBarrierDescriptor::ObjectRegister());
4640 RequireSpecificTemporary(WriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister());
4641}
4642void GeneratorStore::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
4643 const ProcessingState& state) {
4644 Register generator = ToRegister(generator_input());
4645 Register array = WriteBarrierDescriptor::ObjectRegister();
4646 __ LoadTaggedField(array, generator,
4647 JSGeneratorObject::kParametersAndRegistersOffset);
4648
4649 RegisterSnapshot register_snapshot_during_store = register_snapshot();
4650 // Include the array and generator registers in the register snapshot while
4651 // storing parameters and registers, to avoid the write barrier clobbering
4652 // them.
4653 register_snapshot_during_store.live_registers.set(array);
4654 register_snapshot_during_store.live_tagged_registers.set(array);
4655 register_snapshot_during_store.live_registers.set(generator);
4656 register_snapshot_during_store.live_tagged_registers.set(generator);
4657 for (int i = 0; i < num_parameters_and_registers(); i++) {
4658 // Use WriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister() as the temporary for
4659 // the value -- it'll be clobbered by StoreTaggedFieldWithWriteBarrier since
4660 // it's not in the register snapshot, but that's ok, and a clobberable value
4661 // register lets the write barrier emit slightly better code.
4662 Input value_input = parameters_and_registers(i);
4663 Register value = __ FromAnyToRegister(
4664 value_input, WriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister());
4665 // Include the value register in the live set, in case it is used by future
4666 // inputs.
4667 register_snapshot_during_store.live_registers.set(value);
4668 register_snapshot_during_store.live_tagged_registers.set(value);
4669 __ StoreTaggedFieldWithWriteBarrier(
4670 array, FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(i), value,
4671 register_snapshot_during_store,
4672 value_input.node()->decompresses_tagged_result()
4673 ? MaglevAssembler::kValueIsDecompressed
4674 : MaglevAssembler::kValueIsCompressed,
4675 MaglevAssembler::kValueCanBeSmi);
4676 }
4677
4678 __ StoreTaggedSignedField(generator, JSGeneratorObject::kContinuationOffset,
4679 Smi::FromInt(suspend_id()));
4680 __ StoreTaggedSignedField(generator,
4681 JSGeneratorObject::kInputOrDebugPosOffset,
4682 Smi::FromInt(bytecode_offset()));
4683
4684 // Use WriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister() as the scratch
4685 // register, see comment above. At this point we no longer need to preserve
4686 // the array or generator registers, so use the original register snapshot.
4687 Register context = __ FromAnyToRegister(
4688 context_input(), WriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister());
4689 __ StoreTaggedFieldWithWriteBarrier(
4690 generator, JSGeneratorObject::kContextOffset, context,
4691 register_snapshot(),
4692 context_input().node()->decompresses_tagged_result()
4693 ? MaglevAssembler::kValueIsDecompressed
4694 : MaglevAssembler::kValueIsCompressed,
4695 MaglevAssembler::kValueCannotBeSmi);
4696}

4721void Int32ToNumber::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
4722 UseRegister(input());
4723 DefineAsRegister(this);
4724}
4725void Int32ToNumber::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
4726 const ProcessingState& state) {
4727 Register object = ToRegister(result());
4728 Register value = ToRegister(input());
4729 ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
4730 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
4731 // Object is not allowed to alias value, because SmiTagInt32AndJumpIfFail will
4732 // clobber `object` even if the tagging fails, and we don't want it to clobber
4733 // `value`.
4734 bool input_output_alias = (object == value);
4735 Register res = object;
4736 if (input_output_alias) {
4737 res = temps.AcquireScratch();
4738 }
4739 __ SmiTagInt32AndJumpIfFail(
4740 res, value,
4741 __ MakeDeferredCode(
4742 [](MaglevAssembler* masm, Register object, Register value,
4743 Register scratch, ZoneLabelRef done, Int32ToNumber* node) {
4744 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
4745 // AllocateHeapNumber needs a scratch register, and the res scratch
4746 // register isn't needed anymore, so return it to the pool.
4747 if (scratch.is_valid()) {
4748 temps.IncludeScratch(scratch);
4749 }
4750 DoubleRegister double_value = temps.AcquireScratchDouble();
4751 __ Int32ToDouble(double_value, value);
4752 __ AllocateHeapNumber(node->register_snapshot(), object,
4753 double_value);
4754 __ Jump(*done);
4755 },
4756 object, value, input_output_alias ? res : Register::no_reg(), done,
4757 this));
4758 if (input_output_alias) {
4759 __ Move(object, res);
4760 }
4761 __ bind(*done);
4762}

4764void Uint32ToNumber::SetValueLocationConstraints() {

4768 DefineSameAsFirst(this);
4769#else
4770 DefineAsRegister(this);
4771#endif
4772}
4773void Uint32ToNumber::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
4774 const ProcessingState& state) {
4775 ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
4776 Register value = ToRegister(input());
4777 Register object = ToRegister(result());
4778 // Unlike Int32ToNumber, object is allowed to alias value here (indeed, the
4779 // code is better if it does). The difference is that Uint32 smi tagging first
4780 // does a range check, and doesn't clobber `object` on failure.
4781 __ SmiTagUint32AndJumpIfFail(
4782 object, value,
4783 __ MakeDeferredCode(
4784 [](MaglevAssembler* masm, Register object, Register value,
4785 ZoneLabelRef done, Uint32ToNumber* node) {
4786 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
4787 DoubleRegister double_value = temps.AcquireScratchDouble();
4788 __ Uint32ToDouble(double_value, value);
4789 __ AllocateHeapNumber(node->register_snapshot(), object,
4790 double_value);
4791 __ Jump(*done);
4792 },
4793 object, value, done, this));
4794 __ bind(*done);
4795}

4963int BuiltinStringPrototypeCharCodeOrCodePointAt::MaxCallStackArgs() const {
4964 DCHECK_EQ(Runtime::FunctionForId(Runtime::kStringCharCodeAt)->nargs, 2);
4965 return 2;
4966}
4967void BuiltinStringPrototypeCharCodeOrCodePointAt::
4968 SetValueLocationConstraints() {
4969 UseAndClobberRegister(string_input());
4970 UseAndClobberRegister(index_input());
4971 DefineAsRegister(this);
4972 // TODO(victorgomes): Add a mode to the register allocator where we ensure
4973 // input cannot alias with output. We can then remove the second scratch.
4974 set_temporaries_needed(
4975 mode_ == BuiltinStringPrototypeCharCodeOrCodePointAt::kCodePointAt ? 2
4976 : 1);
4977}
4978void BuiltinStringPrototypeCharCodeOrCodePointAt::GenerateCode(
4979 MaglevAssembler* masm, const ProcessingState& state) {
4980 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
4981 Register scratch1 = temps.Acquire();
4982 Register scratch2 = Register::no_reg();
4983 if (mode_ == BuiltinStringPrototypeCharCodeOrCodePointAt::kCodePointAt) {
4984 scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
4985 }
4986 Register string = ToRegister(string_input());
4987 Register index = ToRegister(index_input());
4988 ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
4989 RegisterSnapshot save_registers = register_snapshot();
4990 __ StringCharCodeOrCodePointAt(mode_, save_registers, ToRegister(result()),
4991 string, index, scratch1, scratch2, *done);
4992 __ bind(*done);
4993}

5027
5028void StringWrapperConcat::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
5029 const ProcessingState& state) {
5030 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
5031
5032 Register left = ToRegister(lhs());
5033 Label left_done;
5034 __ JumpIfString(left, &left_done);
5035 __ LoadTaggedField(left, left, JSPrimitiveWrapper::kValueOffset);
5036 __ Jump(&left_done);
5037
5038 __ bind(&left_done);
5039
5040 Register right = ToRegister(rhs());
5041 Label right_done;
5042 __ JumpIfString(right, &right_done);
5043 __ LoadTaggedField(right, right, JSPrimitiveWrapper::kValueOffset);
5044 __ Jump(&right_done);
5045
5046 __ bind(&right_done);
5047
5048 __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kStringAdd_CheckNone>(
5049 masm->native_context().object(), // context
5050 left, // left
5051 right // right
5052 );
5053 masm->DefineExceptionHandlerAndLazyDeoptPoint(this);
5054 DCHECK_EQ(kReturnRegister0, ToRegister(result()));
5055}
5056
5057void StringEqual::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
5058 using D = StringEqualDescriptor;
5059 UseFixed(lhs(), D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kLeft));
5060 UseFixed(rhs(), D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kRight));
5061 set_temporaries_needed(1);
5062 RequireSpecificTemporary(D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kLength));
5063 DefineAsFixed(this, kReturnRegister0);
5064}
5065void StringEqual::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
5066 const ProcessingState& state) {
5067 using D = StringEqualDescriptor;
5068 Label done, if_equal, if_not_equal;
5069 Register left = ToRegister(lhs());
5070 Register right = ToRegister(rhs());
5071 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
5072 Register left_length = temps.Acquire();
5073 Register right_length = D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kLength);
5074
5075 __ CmpTagged(left, right);
5076 __ JumpIf(kEqual, &if_equal,
5077 // Debug checks in StringLength can make this jump too long for a
5078 // near jump.
5079 v8_flags.debug_code ? Label::kFar : Label::kNear);
5080
5081 __ StringLength(left_length, left);
5082 __ StringLength(right_length, right);
5083 __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(left_length, right_length, kNotEqual, &if_not_equal,
5084 Label::Distance::kNear);
5085
5086 // The inputs are already in the right registers. The |left| and |right|
5087 // inputs were required to come in in the left/right inputs of the builtin,
5088 // and the |length| input of the builtin is where we loaded the length of the
5089 // right string (which matches the length of the left string when we get
5090 // here).
5091 DCHECK_EQ(right_length, D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kLength));
5092 __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kStringEqual>(lhs(), rhs(),
5093 D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kLength));
5094 masm->DefineLazyDeoptPoint(this->lazy_deopt_info());
5095 __ Jump(&done, Label::Distance::kNear);
5096
5097 __ bind(&if_equal);
5098 __ LoadRoot(ToRegister(result()), RootIndex::kTrueValue);
5099 __ Jump(&done, Label::Distance::kNear);
5100
5101 __ bind(&if_not_equal);
5102 __ LoadRoot(ToRegister(result()), RootIndex::kFalseValue);
5103
5104 __ bind(&done);
5105}

5249int ToNumberOrNumeric::MaxCallStackArgs() const {
5250 return TypeConversionDescriptor::GetStackParameterCount();
5251}
5252void ToNumberOrNumeric::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
5253 UseRegister(value_input());
5254 set_temporaries_needed(1);
5255 DefineAsRegister(this);
5256}
5257void ToNumberOrNumeric::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
5258 const ProcessingState& state) {
5259 ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
5260 Label move_and_return;
5261 Register object = ToRegister(value_input());
5262 Register result_reg = ToRegister(result());
5263
5264 __ JumpIfSmi(object, &move_and_return, Label::kNear);
5265 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
5266 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5267 __ CompareMapWithRoot(object, RootIndex::kHeapNumberMap, scratch);
5268 __ JumpToDeferredIf(
5269 kNotEqual,
5270 [](MaglevAssembler* masm, Object::Conversion mode, Register object,
5271 Register result_reg, ToNumberOrNumeric* node, ZoneLabelRef done) {
5272 {
5273 RegisterSnapshot snapshot = node->register_snapshot();
5274 snapshot.live_registers.clear(result_reg);
5275 SaveRegisterStateForCall save_register_state(masm, snapshot);
5276 switch (mode) {
5277 case Object::Conversion::kToNumber:
5278 __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kToNumber>(
5279 masm->native_context().object(), object);
5280 break;
5281 case Object::Conversion::kToNumeric:
5282 __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kToNumeric>(
5283 masm->native_context().object(), object);
5284 break;
5285 }
5286 masm->DefineExceptionHandlerPoint(node);
5287 save_register_state.DefineSafepointWithLazyDeopt(
5288 node->lazy_deopt_info());
5289 __ Move(result_reg, kReturnRegister0);
5290 }
5291 __ Jump(*done);
5292 },
5293 mode(), object, result_reg, this, done);
5294 __ bind(&move_and_return);
5295 __ Move(result_reg, object);
5296
5297 __ bind(*done);
5298}

5310void ToObject::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
5311 const ProcessingState& state) {
5312 Register value = ToRegister(value_input());
5313 Label call_builtin, done;
5314 // Avoid the builtin call if {value} is a JSReceiver.
5315 if (check_type() == CheckType::kOmitHeapObjectCheck) {
5316 __ AssertNotSmi(value);
5317 } else {
5318 __ JumpIfSmi(value, &call_builtin, Label::Distance::kNear);
5319 }
5320 __ JumpIfJSAnyIsNotPrimitive(value, &done, Label::Distance::kNear);
5321 __ bind(&call_builtin);
5322 __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kToObject>(context(), // context
5323 value_input() // input
5324 );
5325 masm->DefineExceptionHandlerAndLazyDeoptPoint(this);
5326 __ bind(&done);
5327}

5592 Register value = ToRegister(input());
5593 DCHECK_EQ(value, ToRegister(result()));
5594 Label done;
5595 __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(value, 255, kUnsignedLessThanEqual, &done,
5596 Label::Distance::kNear);
5597 __ Move(value, 255);
5598 __ bind(&done);
5599}
5600
5601void Float64ToUint8Clamped::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
5602 UseRegister(input());
5603 DefineAsRegister(this);
5604}
5605void Float64ToUint8Clamped::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
5606 const ProcessingState& state) {
5607 DoubleRegister value = ToDoubleRegister(input());
5608 Register result_reg = ToRegister(result());
5609 Label min, max, done;
5610 __ ToUint8Clamped(result_reg, value, &min, &max, &done);
5611 __ bind(&min);
5612 __ Move(result_reg, 0);
5613 __ Jump(&done, Label::Distance::kNear);
5614 __ bind(&max);
5615 __ Move(result_reg, 255);
5616 __ bind(&done);
5617}
5618
5619void CheckNumber::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
5620 UseRegister(receiver_input());
5621}
5622void CheckNumber::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
5623 const ProcessingState& state) {
5624 Label done;
5625 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
5626 Register scratch = temps.AcquireScratch();
5627 Register value = ToRegister(receiver_input());
5628 // If {value} is a Smi or a HeapNumber, we're done.
5629 __ JumpIfSmi(
5630 value, &done,
5631 v8_flags.debug_code ? Label::Distance::kFar : Label::Distance::kNear);
5632 if (mode() == Object::Conversion::kToNumeric) {
5633 __ LoadMapForCompare(scratch, value);
5634 __ CompareTaggedRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kHeapNumberMap);
5635 // Jump to done if it is a HeapNumber.
5636 __ JumpIf(
5637 kEqual, &done,
5638 v8_flags.debug_code ? Label::Distance::kFar : Label::Distance::kNear);
5639 // Check if it is a BigInt.
5640 __ CompareTaggedRootAndEmitEagerDeoptIf(
5641 scratch, RootIndex::kBigIntMap, kNotEqual,
5642 DeoptimizeReason::kNotANumber, this);
5643 } else {
5644 __ CompareMapWithRootAndEmitEagerDeoptIf(
5645 value, RootIndex::kHeapNumberMap, scratch, kNotEqual,
5646 DeoptimizeReason::kNotANumber, this);
5647 }
5648 __ bind(&done);
5649}
5650
5651void CheckedInternalizedString::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
5652 UseRegister(object_input());
5653 DefineSameAsFirst(this);
5654}
5655void CheckedInternalizedString::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
5656 const ProcessingState& state) {
5657 Register object = ToRegister(object_input());
5658 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
5659 Register instance_type = temps.AcquireScratch();
5660 if (check_type() == CheckType::kOmitHeapObjectCheck) {
5661 __ AssertNotSmi(object);
5662 } else {
5663 __ EmitEagerDeoptIfSmi(this, object, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap);
5664 }
5665 __ LoadInstanceType(instance_type, object);
5666 __ RecordComment("Test IsInternalizedString");
5667 // Go to the slow path if this is a non-string, or a non-internalised string.
5668 static_assert((kStringTag | kInternalizedTag) == 0);
5669 ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
5670 __ TestInt32AndJumpIfAnySet(
5671 instance_type, kIsNotStringMask | kIsNotInternalizedMask,
5672 __ MakeDeferredCode(
5673 [](MaglevAssembler* masm, ZoneLabelRef done,
5674 CheckedInternalizedString* node, Register object,
5675 Register instance_type) {
5676 __ RecordComment("Deferred Test IsThinString");
5677 // Deopt if this isn't a string.
5678 __ TestInt32AndJumpIfAnySet(
5679 instance_type, kIsNotStringMask,
5680 __ GetDeoptLabel(node, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap));
5681 // Deopt if this isn't a thin string.
5682 __ AndInt32(instance_type, kStringRepresentationMask);
5683 __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(
5684 instance_type, kThinStringTag, kNotEqual,
5685 __ GetDeoptLabel(node, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap));
5686 // Load internalized string from thin string.
5687 __ LoadTaggedField(object, object, offsetof(ThinString, actual_));
5688 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
5689 __ RecordComment("DCHECK IsInternalizedString");
5690 Label checked;
5691 __ LoadInstanceType(instance_type, object);
5692 __ TestInt32AndJumpIfAllClear(
5693 instance_type, kIsNotStringMask | kIsNotInternalizedMask,
5694 &checked);
5695 __ Abort(AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
5696 __ bind(&checked);
5697 }
5698 __ Jump(*done);
5699 },
5700 done, this, object, instance_type));
5701 __ bind(*done);
5702}
5703
5704void CheckedNumberToUint8Clamped::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
5705 UseRegister(input());
5706 DefineSameAsFirst(this);
5707 set_temporaries_needed(1);
5708 set_double_temporaries_needed(1);
5709}
5710void CheckedNumberToUint8Clamped::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
5711 const ProcessingState& state) {
5712 Register value = ToRegister(input());
5713 Register result_reg = ToRegister(result());
5714 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
5715 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5716 DoubleRegister double_value = temps.AcquireDouble();
5717 Label is_not_smi, min, max, done;
5718 // Check if Smi.
5719 __ JumpIfNotSmi(value, &is_not_smi);
5720 // If Smi, convert to Int32.
5721 __ SmiToInt32(value);
5722 // Clamp.
5723 __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(value, 0, kLessThanEqual, &min);
5724 __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(value, 255, kGreaterThanEqual, &max);
5725 __ Jump(&done);
5726 __ bind(&is_not_smi);
5727 // Check if HeapNumber, deopt otherwise.
5728 __ CompareMapWithRootAndEmitEagerDeoptIf(value, RootIndex::kHeapNumberMap,
5729 scratch, kNotEqual,
5730 DeoptimizeReason::kNotANumber, this);
5731 // If heap number, get double value.
5732 __ LoadHeapNumberValue(double_value, value);
5733 // Clamp.
5734 __ ToUint8Clamped(value, double_value, &min, &max, &done);
5735 __ bind(&min);
5736 __ Move(result_reg, 0);
5737 __ Jump(&done, Label::Distance::kNear);
5738 __ bind(&max);
5739 __ Move(result_reg, 255);
5740 __ bind(&done);
5741}

5777void Call::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
5778 using D = CallTrampolineDescriptor;
5779 UseFixed(function(), D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kFunction));
5780 UseAny(arg(0));
5781 for (int i = 1; i < num_args(); i++) {
5782 UseAny(arg(i));
5783 }
5784 UseFixed(context(), kContextRegister);
5785 DefineAsFixed(this, kReturnRegister0);
5786}
5787
5788void Call::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm, const ProcessingState& state) {
5789 __ PushReverse(args());
5790
5791 uint32_t arg_count = num_args();
5792 if (target_type_ == TargetType::kAny) {
5793 switch (receiver_mode_) {
5794 case ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined:
5795 __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kCall_ReceiverIsNullOrUndefined>(
5796 context(), function(), arg_count);
5797 break;
5798 case ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined:
5799 __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kCall_ReceiverIsNotNullOrUndefined>(
5800 context(), function(), arg_count);
5801 break;
5802 case ConvertReceiverMode::kAny:
5803 __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kCall_ReceiverIsAny>(context(), function(),
5804 arg_count);
5805 break;
5806 }
5807 } else {
5808 DCHECK_EQ(TargetType::kJSFunction, target_type_);
5809 switch (receiver_mode_) {
5810 case ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined:
5811 __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kCallFunction_ReceiverIsNullOrUndefined>(
5812 context(), function(), arg_count);
5813 break;
5814 case ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined:
5815 __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kCallFunction_ReceiverIsNotNullOrUndefined>(
5816 context(), function(), arg_count);
5817 break;
5818 case ConvertReceiverMode::kAny:
5819 __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kCallFunction_ReceiverIsAny>(
5820 context(), function(), arg_count);
5821 break;
5822 }
5823 }
5824
5825 masm->DefineExceptionHandlerAndLazyDeoptPoint(this);
5826}

5860void CallSelf::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
5861 UseAny(receiver());
5862 for (int i = 0; i < num_args(); i++) {
5863 UseAny(arg(i));
5864 }
5865 UseFixed(closure(), kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister);
5866 UseFixed(new_target(), kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister);
5867 UseFixed(context(), kContextRegister);

5871
5872void CallSelf::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
5873 const ProcessingState& state) {
5874 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
5875 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5876 int actual_parameter_count = num_args() + 1;
5877 if (actual_parameter_count < expected_parameter_count_) {
5878 int number_of_undefineds =
5879 expected_parameter_count_ - actual_parameter_count;
5880 __ LoadRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
5881 __ PushReverse(receiver(), args(),
5882 RepeatValue(scratch, number_of_undefineds));
5883 } else {
5884 __ PushReverse(receiver(), args());
5885 }
5886 DCHECK_EQ(kContextRegister, ToRegister(context()));
5887 DCHECK_EQ(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister, ToRegister(closure()));
5888 __ Move(kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister, actual_parameter_count);
5889 __ CallSelf();
5890 masm->DefineExceptionHandlerAndLazyDeoptPoint(this);
5891}

5899 for (int i = 0; i < num_args(); i++) {
5900 UseAny(arg(i));
5901 }

5904 UseFixed(context(), kContextRegister);

5908
5909void CallKnownJSFunction::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
5910 const ProcessingState& state) {
5911 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
5912 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5913 int actual_parameter_count = num_args() + 1;
5914 if (actual_parameter_count < expected_parameter_count_) {
5915 int number_of_undefineds =
5916 expected_parameter_count_ - actual_parameter_count;
5917 __ LoadRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
5918 __ PushReverse(receiver(), args(),
5919 RepeatValue(scratch, number_of_undefineds));
5920 } else {
5921 __ PushReverse(receiver(), args());
5922 }
5923 // From here on, we're going to do a call, so all registers are valid temps,
5924 // except for the ones we're going to write. This is needed in case one of the
5925 // helper methods below wants to use a temp and one of these is in the temp
5926 // list (in particular, this can happen on arm64 where cp is a temp register
5927 // by default).
5928 temps.SetAvailable(MaglevAssembler::GetAllocatableRegisters() -
5929 RegList{kContextRegister, kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister,
5930 kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister,
5931 kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister,
5932 kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister});
5933 DCHECK_EQ(kContextRegister, ToRegister(context()));
5934 DCHECK_EQ(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister, ToRegister(closure()));
5935 __ Move(kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister, actual_parameter_count);
5936 if (shared_function_info().HasBuiltinId()) {
5937 Builtin builtin = shared_function_info().builtin_id();
5938
5939 // This SBXCHECK is a defense-in-depth measure to ensure that we always
5940 // generate valid calls here (with matching signatures).
5941 SBXCHECK_EQ(expected_parameter_count_,
5942 Builtins::GetFormalParameterCount(builtin));
5943
5944 __ CallBuiltin(builtin);
5945 } else {
5946#if V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
5947 __ CallJSDispatchEntry(dispatch_handle_, expected_parameter_count_);
5948#else
5949 __ CallJSFunction(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister, expected_parameter_count_);
5950#endif
5951 }
5952 masm->DefineExceptionHandlerAndLazyDeoptPoint(this);
5953}

5955int CallKnownApiFunction::MaxCallStackArgs() const {
5956 int actual_parameter_count = num_args() + 1;
5957 return actual_parameter_count;
5958}
5959
5960void CallKnownApiFunction::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
5961 if (api_holder_.has_value()) {
5962 UseAny(receiver());
5963 } else {
5964 // This is an "Api holder is receiver" case, ask register allocator to put
5965 // receiver value into the right register.
5966 UseFixed(receiver(), CallApiCallbackOptimizedDescriptor::HolderRegister());
5967 }
5968 for (int i = 0; i < num_args(); i++) {
5969 UseAny(arg(i));
5970 }
5971 UseFixed(context(), kContextRegister);
5972
5973 DefineAsFixed(this, kReturnRegister0);
5974
5975 if (inline_builtin()) {
5976 set_temporaries_needed(2);
5977 }
5978}
5979
5980void CallKnownApiFunction::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
5981 const ProcessingState& state) {
5982 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
5983 __ PushReverse(receiver(), args());
5984
5985 // From here on, we're going to do a call, so all registers are valid temps,
5986 // except for the ones we're going to write. This is needed in case one of the
5987 // helper methods below wants to use a temp and one of these is in the temp
5988 // list (in particular, this can happen on arm64 where cp is a temp register
5989 // by default).
5990 temps.SetAvailable(
5991 kAllocatableGeneralRegisters -
5992 RegList{
5993 kContextRegister,
5994 CallApiCallbackOptimizedDescriptor::HolderRegister(),
5995 CallApiCallbackOptimizedDescriptor::ActualArgumentsCountRegister(),
5996 CallApiCallbackOptimizedDescriptor::FunctionTemplateInfoRegister(),
5997 CallApiCallbackOptimizedDescriptor::ApiFunctionAddressRegister()});
5998 DCHECK_EQ(kContextRegister, ToRegister(context()));
5999
6000 if (inline_builtin()) {
6001 GenerateCallApiCallbackOptimizedInline(masm, state);
6002 return;
6003 }
6004
6005 if (api_holder_.has_value()) {
6006 __ Move(CallApiCallbackOptimizedDescriptor::HolderRegister(),
6007 api_holder_.value().object());
6008 } else {
6009 // This is an "Api holder is receiver" case, register allocator was asked
6010 // to put receiver value into the right register.
6011 DCHECK_EQ(CallApiCallbackOptimizedDescriptor::HolderRegister(),
6012 ToRegister(receiver()));
6013 }
6014 __ Move(CallApiCallbackOptimizedDescriptor::ActualArgumentsCountRegister(),
6015 num_args()); // not including receiver
6016
6017 __ Move(CallApiCallbackOptimizedDescriptor::FunctionTemplateInfoRegister(),
6018 i::Cast<HeapObject>(function_template_info_.object()));
6019
6020 compiler::JSHeapBroker* broker = masm->compilation_info()->broker();
6021 ApiFunction function(function_template_info_.callback(broker));
6022 ExternalReference reference =
6023 ExternalReference::Create(&function, ExternalReference::DIRECT_API_CALL);
6024 __ Move(CallApiCallbackOptimizedDescriptor::ApiFunctionAddressRegister(),
6025 reference);
6026
6027 switch (mode()) {
6028 case kNoProfiling:
6029 __ CallBuiltin(Builtin::kCallApiCallbackOptimizedNoProfiling);
6030 break;
6031 case kNoProfilingInlined:
6032 UNREACHABLE();
6033 case kGeneric:
6034 __ CallBuiltin(Builtin::kCallApiCallbackOptimized);
6035 break;
6036 }
6037 masm->DefineExceptionHandlerAndLazyDeoptPoint(this);
6038}
6039
6040void CallKnownApiFunction::GenerateCallApiCallbackOptimizedInline(
6041 MaglevAssembler* masm, const ProcessingState& state) {
6042 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
6043 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6044 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
6045
6046 using FCA = FunctionCallbackArguments;
6047 using ER = ExternalReference;
6048 using FC = ApiCallbackExitFrameConstants;
6049
6050 static_assert(FCA::kArgsLength == 6);
6051 static_assert(FCA::kNewTargetIndex == 5);
6052 static_assert(FCA::kTargetIndex == 4);
6053 static_assert(FCA::kReturnValueIndex == 3);
6054 static_assert(FCA::kContextIndex == 2);
6055 static_assert(FCA::kIsolateIndex == 1);
6056 static_assert(FCA::kHolderIndex == 0);
6057
6058 // Set up FunctionCallbackInfo's implicit_args on the stack as follows:
6059 //
6060 // Target state:
6061 // sp[0 * kSystemPointerSize]: kHolder <= implicit_args_
6062 // sp[1 * kSystemPointerSize]: kIsolate
6063 // sp[2 * kSystemPointerSize]: kContext
6064 // sp[3 * kSystemPointerSize]: undefined (kReturnValue)
6065 // sp[4 * kSystemPointerSize]: kTarget
6066 // sp[5 * kSystemPointerSize]: undefined (kNewTarget)
6067 // Existing state:
6068 // sp[6 * kSystemPointerSize]: <= FCA:::values_
6069
6070 __ StoreRootRelative(IsolateData::topmost_script_having_context_offset(),
6071 kContextRegister);
6072
6073 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm, "inlined CallApiCallbackOptimized builtin");
6074 __ LoadRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
6075 // kNewTarget, kTarget, kReturnValue, kContext
6076 __ Push(scratch, i::Cast<HeapObject>(function_template_info_.object()),
6077 scratch, kContextRegister);
6078 __ Move(scratch, ER::isolate_address());
6079 // kIsolate, kHolder
6080 if (api_holder_.has_value()) {
6081 __ Push(scratch, api_holder_.value().object());
6082 } else {
6083 // This is an "Api holder is receiver" case, register allocator was asked
6084 // to put receiver value into the right register.
6085 __ Push(scratch, receiver());
6086 }
6087
6088 Register api_function_address =
6089 CallApiCallbackOptimizedDescriptor::ApiFunctionAddressRegister();
6090
6091 compiler::JSHeapBroker* broker = masm->compilation_info()->broker();
6092 ApiFunction function(function_template_info_.callback(broker));
6093 ExternalReference reference =
6094 ExternalReference::Create(&function, ExternalReference::DIRECT_API_CALL);
6095 __ Move(api_function_address, reference);
6096
6097 Label done, call_api_callback_builtin_inline;
6098 __ Call(&call_api_callback_builtin_inline);
6099 masm->DefineExceptionHandlerAndLazyDeoptPoint(this);
6100 __ jmp(&done);
6101
6102 //
6103 // Generate a CallApiCallback builtin inline.
6104 //
6105 __ bind(&call_api_callback_builtin_inline);
6106
6107 FrameScope frame_scope(masm, StackFrame::MANUAL);
6108 __ EmitEnterExitFrame(FC::getExtraSlotsCountFrom<ExitFrameConstants>(),
6109 StackFrame::API_CALLBACK_EXIT, api_function_address,
6110 scratch2);
6111
6112 Register fp = __ GetFramePointer();
6113#ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM64
6114 // This is a workaround for performance regression observed on Apple Silicon
6115 // (https://crbug.com/347741609): reading argc value after the call via
6116 // MemOperand argc_operand = MemOperand(fp, FC::kFCIArgcOffset);
6117 // is noticeably slower than using sp-based access:
6118 MemOperand argc_operand = ExitFrameStackSlotOperand(FCA::kLengthOffset);
6119#else
6120 // We don't enable this workaround for other configurations because
6121 // a) it's not possible to convert fp-based encoding to sp-based one:
6122 // V8 guarantees stack pointer to be only kSystemPointerSize-aligned,
6123 // while C function might require stack pointer to be 16-byte aligned on
6124 // certain platforms,
6125 // b) local experiments on x64 didn't show improvements.
6126 MemOperand argc_operand = MemOperand(fp, FC::kFCIArgcOffset);
6127#endif // V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM64
6128 {
6129 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm, "Initialize v8::FunctionCallbackInfo");
6130 // FunctionCallbackInfo::length_.
6131 __ Move(scratch, num_args()); // not including receiver
6132 __ Move(argc_operand, scratch);
6133
6134 // FunctionCallbackInfo::implicit_args_.
6135 __ LoadAddress(scratch, MemOperand(fp, FC::kImplicitArgsArrayOffset));
6136 __ Move(MemOperand(fp, FC::kFCIImplicitArgsOffset), scratch);
6137
6138 // FunctionCallbackInfo::values_ (points at JS arguments on the stack).
6139 __ LoadAddress(scratch, MemOperand(fp, FC::kFirstArgumentOffset));
6140 __ Move(MemOperand(fp, FC::kFCIValuesOffset), scratch);
6141 }
6142
6143 Register function_callback_info_arg = kCArgRegs[0];
6144
6145 __ RecordComment("v8::FunctionCallback's argument.");
6146 __ LoadAddress(function_callback_info_arg,
6147 MemOperand(fp, FC::kFunctionCallbackInfoOffset));
6148
6149 DCHECK(!AreAliased(api_function_address, function_callback_info_arg));
6150
6151 MemOperand return_value_operand = MemOperand(fp, FC::kReturnValueOffset);
6152 const int kSlotsToDropOnReturn =
6153 FC::kFunctionCallbackInfoArgsLength + kJSArgcReceiverSlots + num_args();
6154
6155 const bool with_profiling = false;
6156 ExternalReference no_thunk_ref;
6157 Register no_thunk_arg = no_reg;
6158
6159 CallApiFunctionAndReturn(masm, with_profiling, api_function_address,
6160 no_thunk_ref, no_thunk_arg, kSlotsToDropOnReturn,
6161 nullptr, return_value_operand);
6162 __ RecordComment("end of inlined CallApiCallbackOptimized builtin");
6163
6164 __ bind(&done);
6165}
6166
6167int CallBuiltin::MaxCallStackArgs() const {
6168 auto descriptor = Builtins::CallInterfaceDescriptorFor(builtin());
6169 if (!descriptor.AllowVarArgs()) {
6170 return descriptor.GetStackParameterCount();
6171 } else {
6172 int all_input_count = InputCountWithoutContext() + (has_feedback() ? 2 : 0);
6173 DCHECK_GE(all_input_count, descriptor.GetRegisterParameterCount());
6174 return all_input_count - descriptor.GetRegisterParameterCount();
6175 }
6176}
6177
6178void CallBuiltin::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
6179 auto descriptor = Builtins::CallInterfaceDescriptorFor(builtin());
6180 bool has_context = descriptor.HasContextParameter();
6181 int i = 0;
6182 for (; i < InputsInRegisterCount(); i++) {
6183 UseFixed(input(i), descriptor.GetRegisterParameter(i));
6184 }
6185 for (; i < InputCountWithoutContext(); i++) {
6186 UseAny(input(i));
6187 }
6188 if (has_context) {
6189 UseFixed(input(i), kContextRegister);
6190 }
6191 DefineAsFixed(this, kReturnRegister0);
6192}
6193
6194template <typename... Args>
6195void CallBuiltin::PushArguments(MaglevAssembler* masm, Args... extra_args) {
6196 auto descriptor = Builtins::CallInterfaceDescriptorFor(builtin());
6197 if (descriptor.GetStackArgumentOrder() == StackArgumentOrder::kDefault) {
6198 // In Default order we cannot have extra args (feedback).
6199 DCHECK_EQ(sizeof...(extra_args), 0);
6200 __ Push(stack_args());
6201 } else {
6202 DCHECK_EQ(descriptor.GetStackArgumentOrder(), StackArgumentOrder::kJS);
6203 __ PushReverse(extra_args..., stack_args());
6204 }
6205}
6206
6207void CallBuiltin::PassFeedbackSlotInRegister(MaglevAssembler* masm) {
6208 DCHECK(has_feedback());
6209 auto descriptor = Builtins::CallInterfaceDescriptorFor(builtin());
6210 int slot_index = InputCountWithoutContext();
6211 switch (slot_type()) {
6212 case kTaggedIndex:
6213 __ Move(descriptor.GetRegisterParameter(slot_index),
6214 TaggedIndex::FromIntptr(feedback().index()));
6215 break;
6216 case kSmi:
6217 __ Move(descriptor.GetRegisterParameter(slot_index),
6218 Smi::FromInt(feedback().index()));
6219 break;
6220 }
6221}
6222
6223void CallBuiltin::PushFeedbackAndArguments(MaglevAssembler* masm) {
6224 DCHECK(has_feedback());
6225
6226 auto descriptor = Builtins::CallInterfaceDescriptorFor(builtin());
6227 int slot_index = InputCountWithoutContext();
6228 int vector_index = slot_index + 1;
6229
6230 // There are three possibilities:
6231 // 1. Feedback slot and vector are in register.
6232 // 2. Feedback slot is in register and vector is on stack.
6233 // 3. Feedback slot and vector are on stack.
6234 if (vector_index < descriptor.GetRegisterParameterCount()) {
6235 PassFeedbackSlotInRegister(masm);
6236 __ Move(descriptor.GetRegisterParameter(vector_index), feedback().vector);
6237 PushArguments(masm);
6238 } else if (vector_index == descriptor.GetRegisterParameterCount()) {
6239 PassFeedbackSlotInRegister(masm);
6240 DCHECK_EQ(descriptor.GetStackArgumentOrder(), StackArgumentOrder::kJS);
6241 // Ensure that the builtin only expects the feedback vector on the stack and
6242 // potentional additional var args are passed through to another builtin.
6243 // This is required to align the stack correctly (e.g. on arm64).
6244 DCHECK_EQ(descriptor.GetStackParameterCount(), 1);
6245 PushArguments(masm);
6246 __ Push(feedback().vector);
6247 } else {
6248 int slot = feedback().index();
6249 Handle<FeedbackVector> vector = feedback().vector;
6250 switch (slot_type()) {
6251 case kTaggedIndex:
6252 PushArguments(masm, TaggedIndex::FromIntptr(slot), vector);
6253 break;
6254 case kSmi:
6255 PushArguments(masm, Smi::FromInt(slot), vector);
6256 break;
6257 }
6258 }
6259}
6260
6261void CallBuiltin::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
6262 const ProcessingState& state) {
6263 if (has_feedback()) {
6264 PushFeedbackAndArguments(masm);
6265 } else {
6266 PushArguments(masm);
6267 }
6268 __ CallBuiltin(builtin());
6269 masm->DefineExceptionHandlerAndLazyDeoptPoint(this);
6270}

6272int CallCPPBuiltin::MaxCallStackArgs() const {
6273 using D = CallInterfaceDescriptorFor<kCEntry_Builtin>::type;
6274 return D::GetStackParameterCount() + num_args();

6276
6277void CallCPPBuiltin::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
6278 using D = CallInterfaceDescriptorFor<kCEntry_Builtin>::type;
6279 UseAny(target());
6280 UseAny(new_target());
6281 UseFixed(context(), kContextRegister);
6282 for (int i = 0; i < num_args(); i++) {
6283 UseAny(arg(i));
6284 }
6285 DefineAsFixed(this, kReturnRegister0);
6286 set_temporaries_needed(1);
6287 RequireSpecificTemporary(D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kArity));
6288 RequireSpecificTemporary(D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kCFunction));
6289}
6290
6291void CallCPPBuiltin::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
6292 const ProcessingState& state) {
6293 using D = CallInterfaceDescriptorFor<kCEntry_Builtin>::type;
6294 constexpr Register kArityReg = D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kArity);
6295 constexpr Register kCFunctionReg = D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kCFunction);
6296
6297 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
6298 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6299 __ LoadRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
6300
6301 // Push all arguments to the builtin (including the receiver).
6302 static_assert(BuiltinArguments::kReceiverIndex == 4);
6303 __ PushReverse(args());
6304
6305 static_assert(BuiltinArguments::kNumExtraArgs == 4);
6306 static_assert(BuiltinArguments::kNewTargetIndex == 0);
6307 static_assert(BuiltinArguments::kTargetIndex == 1);
6308 static_assert(BuiltinArguments::kArgcIndex == 2);
6309 static_assert(BuiltinArguments::kPaddingIndex == 3);
6310 // Push stack arguments for CEntry.
6311 Tagged<Smi> tagged_argc = Smi::FromInt(BuiltinArguments::kNumExtraArgs +
6312 num_args()); // Includes receiver.
6313 __ Push(scratch /* padding */, tagged_argc, target(), new_target());
6314
6315 // Move values to fixed registers after all arguments are pushed. Registers
6316 // for arguments and CEntry registers might overlap.
6317 __ Move(kArityReg, BuiltinArguments::kNumExtraArgs + num_args());
6318 ExternalReference builtin_address =
6319 ExternalReference::Create(Builtins::CppEntryOf(builtin()));
6320 __ Move(kCFunctionReg, builtin_address);
6321
6322 DCHECK_EQ(Builtins::CallInterfaceDescriptorFor(builtin()).GetReturnCount(),
6323 1);
6324 __ CallBuiltin(Builtin::kCEntry_Return1_ArgvOnStack_BuiltinExit);
6325}

6328void CallRuntime::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
6329 UseFixed(context(), kContextRegister);
6330 for (int i = 0; i < num_args(); i++) {
6331 UseAny(arg(i));
6332 }
6333 DefineAsFixed(this, kReturnRegister0);
6334}
6335void CallRuntime::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
6336 const ProcessingState& state) {
6337 DCHECK_EQ(ToRegister(context()), kContextRegister);
6338 __ Push(args());
6339 __ CallRuntime(function_id(), num_args());
6340 // TODO(victorgomes): Not sure if this is needed for all runtime calls.
6341 masm->DefineExceptionHandlerAndLazyDeoptPoint(this);
6342}

6470
6471void SetPendingMessage::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
6472 const ProcessingState& state) {
6473 Register new_message = ToRegister(value());
6474 Register return_value = ToRegister(result());
6475 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
6476 Register scratch = temps.AcquireScratch();
6477 MemOperand pending_message_operand = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
6478 ExternalReference::address_of_pending_message(masm->isolate()), scratch);
6479 if (new_message != return_value) {
6480 __ Move(return_value, pending_message_operand);
6481 __ Move(pending_message_operand, new_message);
6482 } else {
6483 __ Move(scratch, pending_message_operand);
6484 __ Move(pending_message_operand, new_message);
6485 __ Move(return_value, scratch);
6486 }
6487}

6502 __ LoadTaggedField(heap_number, object, offset());
6503 __ AssertNotSmi(heap_number);
6504 __ StoreHeapNumberValue(value, heap_number);
6505}

6525namespace {
6526
6527template <typename NodeT>
6528void GenerateTransitionElementsKind(
6529 MaglevAssembler* masm, NodeT* node, Register object, Register map,
6530 base::Vector<const compiler::MapRef> transition_sources,
6531 const compiler::MapRef transition_target, ZoneLabelRef done,
6532 std::optional<Register> result_opt) {
6533 DCHECK(!compiler::AnyMapIsHeapNumber(transition_sources));
6534 DCHECK(!IsHeapNumberMap(*transition_target.object()));
6535
6536 for (const compiler::MapRef transition_source : transition_sources) {
6537 bool is_simple = IsSimpleMapChangeTransition(
6538 transition_source.elements_kind(), transition_target.elements_kind());
6539
6540 // TODO(leszeks): If there are a lot of transition source maps, move the
6541 // source into a register and share the deferred code between maps.
6542 __ CompareTaggedAndJumpIf(
6543 map, transition_source.object(), kEqual,
6544 __ MakeDeferredCode(
6545 [](MaglevAssembler* masm, Register object, Register map,
6546 RegisterSnapshot register_snapshot,
6547 compiler::MapRef transition_target, bool is_simple,
6548 ZoneLabelRef done, std::optional<Register> result_opt) {
6549 if (is_simple) {
6550 __ MoveTagged(map, transition_target.object());
6551 __ StoreTaggedFieldWithWriteBarrier(
6552 object, HeapObject::kMapOffset, map, register_snapshot,
6553 MaglevAssembler::kValueIsCompressed,
6554 MaglevAssembler::kValueCannotBeSmi);
6555 } else {
6556 SaveRegisterStateForCall save_state(masm, register_snapshot);
6557 __ Push(object, transition_target.object());
6558 __ Move(kContextRegister, masm->native_context().object());
6559 __ CallRuntime(Runtime::kTransitionElementsKind);
6560 save_state.DefineSafepoint();
6561 }
6562 if (result_opt) {
6563 __ MoveTagged(*result_opt, transition_target.object());
6564 }
6565 __ Jump(*done);
6566 },
6567 object, map, node->register_snapshot(), transition_target,
6568 is_simple, done, result_opt));
6569 }
6570}
6571
6572} // namespace

6574int TransitionElementsKind::MaxCallStackArgs() const {
6575 return std::max(WriteBarrierDescriptor::GetStackParameterCount(), 2);

6578void TransitionElementsKind::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
6579 UseRegister(object_input());
6580 UseRegister(map_input());
6581 DefineAsRegister(this);
6582}
6583
6584void TransitionElementsKind::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
6585 const ProcessingState& state) {
6586 Register object = ToRegister(object_input());
6587 Register map = ToRegister(map_input());
6588 Register result_register = ToRegister(result());
6589
6590 ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
6591
6592 __ AssertNotSmi(object);
6593 GenerateTransitionElementsKind(masm, this, object, map,
6594 base::VectorOf(transition_sources_),
6595 transition_target_, done, result_register);
6596 // No transition happened, return the original map.
6597 __ Move(result_register, map);
6598 __ Jump(*done);
6599 __ bind(*done);
6600}

6611void TransitionElementsKindOrCheckMap::GenerateCode(
6612 MaglevAssembler* masm, const ProcessingState& state) {
6613 Register object = ToRegister(object_input());

6615
6616 ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
6617
6618 __ CompareTaggedAndJumpIf(map, transition_target_.object(), kEqual, *done);
6619
6620 GenerateTransitionElementsKind(masm, this, object, map,
6621 base::VectorOf(transition_sources_),
6622 transition_target_, done, {});
6623 // If we didn't jump to 'done' yet, the transition failed.
6624 __ EmitEagerDeopt(this, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap);
6625 __ bind(*done);
6626}

6667namespace {
6668
6669template <typename ResultReg, typename NodeT>
6670void GenerateTypedArrayLoad(MaglevAssembler* masm, NodeT* node, Register object,
6671 Register index, ResultReg result_reg,
6672 ElementsKind kind) {
6673 __ AssertNotSmi(object);
6674 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6675 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
6676 __ AssertObjectType(object, JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE,
6677 AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
6678 }
6679
6680 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
6681 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6682
6683 Register data_pointer = scratch;
6684 __ BuildTypedArrayDataPointer(data_pointer, object);
6685
6686 int element_size = ElementsKindToByteSize(kind);
6687 MemOperand operand =
6688 __ TypedArrayElementOperand(data_pointer, index, element_size);
6689 if constexpr (std::is_same_v<ResultReg, Register>) {
6690 if (IsSignedIntTypedArrayElementsKind(kind)) {
6691 __ LoadSignedField(result_reg, operand, element_size);
6692 } else {
6693 DCHECK(IsUnsignedIntTypedArrayElementsKind(kind));
6694 __ LoadUnsignedField(result_reg, operand, element_size);
6695 }
6696 } else {
6697#ifdef DEBUG
6698 bool result_reg_is_double = std::is_same_v<ResultReg, DoubleRegister>;
6699 DCHECK(result_reg_is_double);
6700 DCHECK(IsFloatTypedArrayElementsKind(kind));
6701#endif
6702 switch (kind) {
6703 case FLOAT32_ELEMENTS:
6704 __ LoadFloat32(result_reg, operand);
6705 break;
6706 case FLOAT64_ELEMENTS:
6707 __ LoadFloat64(result_reg, operand);
6708 break;
6709 default:
6710 UNREACHABLE();
6711 }
6712 }
6713}
6714
6715template <typename ValueReg, typename NodeT>
6716void GenerateTypedArrayStore(MaglevAssembler* masm, NodeT* node,
6717 Register object, Register index, ValueReg value,
6718 ElementsKind kind) {
6719 __ AssertNotSmi(object);
6720 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6721 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
6722 __ AssertObjectType(object, JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE,
6723 AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
6724 }
6725
6726 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
6727 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6728
6729 Register data_pointer = scratch;
6730 __ BuildTypedArrayDataPointer(data_pointer, object);
6731
6732 int element_size = ElementsKindToByteSize(kind);
6733 MemOperand operand =
6734 __ TypedArrayElementOperand(data_pointer, index, element_size);
6735 if constexpr (std::is_same_v<ValueReg, Register>) {
6736 __ StoreField(operand, value, element_size);
6737 } else {
6738#ifdef DEBUG
6739 bool value_is_double = std::is_same_v<ValueReg, DoubleRegister>;
6740 DCHECK(value_is_double);
6741 DCHECK(IsFloatTypedArrayElementsKind(kind));
6742#endif
6743 switch (kind) {
6744 case FLOAT32_ELEMENTS:
6745 __ StoreFloat32(operand, value);
6746 break;
6747 case FLOAT64_ELEMENTS:
6748 __ StoreFloat64(operand, value);
6749 break;
6750 default:
6751 UNREACHABLE();
6752 }
6753 }
6754}

6830 TryOnStackReplacement* node, Register scratch0,
6831 Register scratch1, int32_t loop_depth,
6832 FeedbackSlot feedback_slot,
6833 BytecodeOffset osr_offset) {
6834 // Two cases may cause us to attempt OSR, in the following order:
6835 //
6836 // 1) Presence of cached OSR Turbofan code.
6837 // 2) The OSR urgency exceeds the current loop depth - in that case, call
6838 // into runtime to trigger a Turbofan OSR compilation. A non-zero return
6839 // value means we should deopt into Ignition which will handle all further
6840 // necessary steps (rewriting the stack frame, jumping to OSR'd code).
6841 //
6842 // See also: InterpreterAssembler::OnStackReplacement.
6843
6844 __ AssertFeedbackVector(scratch0, scratch1);
6845
6846 // Case 1).
6847 Label deopt;
6848 Register maybe_target_code = scratch1;
6849 __ TryLoadOptimizedOsrCode(scratch1, CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS, scratch0,
6850 feedback_slot, &deopt, Label::kFar);
6851
6852 // Case 2).
6853 {
6854 __ LoadByte(scratch0,
6855 FieldMemOperand(scratch0, FeedbackVector::kOsrStateOffset));
6856 __ DecodeField<FeedbackVector::OsrUrgencyBits>(scratch0);
6857 __ JumpIfByte(kUnsignedLessThanEqual, scratch0, loop_depth,
6858 *no_code_for_osr);
6859
6860 // The osr_urgency exceeds the current loop_depth, signaling an OSR
6861 // request. Call into runtime to compile.
6862 {
6863 RegisterSnapshot snapshot = node->register_snapshot();
6864 DCHECK(!snapshot.live_registers.has(maybe_target_code));
6865 SaveRegisterStateForCall save_register_state(masm, snapshot);
6866 if (node->unit()->is_inline()) {
6867 // See comment in
6868 // MaglevGraphBuilder::ShouldEmitOsrInterruptBudgetChecks.
6869 CHECK(!node->unit()->is_osr());
6870 __ Push(Smi::FromInt(osr_offset.ToInt()), node->closure());
6871 __ Move(kContextRegister, masm->native_context().object());
6872 __ CallRuntime(Runtime::kCompileOptimizedOSRFromMaglevInlined, 2);
6873 } else {
6874 __ Push(Smi::FromInt(osr_offset.ToInt()));
6875 __ Move(kContextRegister, masm->native_context().object());
6876 __ CallRuntime(Runtime::kCompileOptimizedOSRFromMaglev, 1);
6877 }
6878 save_register_state.DefineSafepoint();
6879 __ Move(maybe_target_code, kReturnRegister0);
6880 }
6881
6882 // A `0` return value means there is no OSR code available yet. Continue
6883 // execution in Maglev, OSR code will be picked up once it exists and is
6884 // cached on the feedback vector.
6885 __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(maybe_target_code, 0, kEqual, *no_code_for_osr);
6886 }
6887
6888 __ bind(&deopt);
6889 if (V8_LIKELY(v8_flags.turbofan)) {
6890 // None of the mutated input registers should be a register input into the
6891 // eager deopt info.
6892 DCHECK_REGLIST_EMPTY(
6893 RegList{scratch0, scratch1} &
6894 GetGeneralRegistersUsedAsInputs(node->eager_deopt_info()));
6895 __ EmitEagerDeopt(node, DeoptimizeReason::kPrepareForOnStackReplacement);
6896 } else {
6897 // Continue execution in Maglev. With TF disabled we cannot OSR and thus it
6898 // doesn't make sense to start the process. We do still perform all
6899 // remaining bookkeeping above though, to keep Maglev code behavior roughly
6900 // the same in both configurations.
6901 __ Jump(*no_code_for_osr);
6902 }
6903}
6904
6905} // namespace
6906
6907int TryOnStackReplacement::MaxCallStackArgs() const {
6908 // For the kCompileOptimizedOSRFromMaglev call.
6909 if (unit()->is_inline()) return 2;
6910 return 1;
6911}
6912void TryOnStackReplacement::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
6913 UseAny(closure());
6914 set_temporaries_needed(2);
6915}
6916void TryOnStackReplacement::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
6917 const ProcessingState& state) {
6918 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
6919 Register scratch0 = temps.Acquire();
6920 Register scratch1 = temps.Acquire();
6921
6922 const Register osr_state = scratch1;
6923 __ Move(scratch0, unit_->feedback().object());
6924 __ AssertFeedbackVector(scratch0, scratch1);
6925 __ LoadByte(osr_state,
6926 FieldMemOperand(scratch0, FeedbackVector::kOsrStateOffset));
6927
6928 ZoneLabelRef no_code_for_osr(masm);
6929
6930 if (v8_flags.maglev_osr) {
6931 // In case we use maglev_osr, we need to explicitly know if there is
6932 // turbofan code waiting for us (i.e., ignore the MaybeHasMaglevOsrCodeBit).
6933 __ DecodeField<
6934 base::BitFieldUnion<FeedbackVector::OsrUrgencyBits,
6935 FeedbackVector::MaybeHasTurbofanOsrCodeBit>>(
6936 osr_state);
6937 }
6938
6939 // The quick initial OSR check. If it passes, we proceed on to more
6940 // expensive OSR logic.
6941 static_assert(FeedbackVector::MaybeHasTurbofanOsrCodeBit::encode(true) >
6942 FeedbackVector::kMaxOsrUrgency);
6943 __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(
6944 osr_state, loop_depth_, kUnsignedGreaterThan,
6945 __ MakeDeferredCode(AttemptOnStackReplacement, no_code_for_osr, this,
6946 scratch0, scratch1, loop_depth_, feedback_slot_,
6947 osr_offset_));
6948 __ bind(*no_code_for_osr);
6949}

6989 false_label, fallthrough_when_true);

7017void BranchIfFloat64IsHole::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
7018 UseRegister(condition_input());
7019 set_temporaries_needed(1);
7020}
7021void BranchIfFloat64IsHole::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
7022 const ProcessingState& state) {
7023 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
7024 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7025 DoubleRegister input = ToDoubleRegister(condition_input());
7026 // See MaglevAssembler::Branch.
7027 bool fallthrough_when_true = if_true() == state.next_block();
7028 bool fallthrough_when_false = if_false() == state.next_block();
7029 if (fallthrough_when_false) {
7030 if (fallthrough_when_true) {
7031 // If both paths are a fallthrough, do nothing.
7032 DCHECK_EQ(if_true(), if_false());
7033 return;
7034 }
7035 // Jump over the false block if true, otherwise fall through into it.
7036 __ JumpIfHoleNan(input, scratch, if_true()->label(), Label::kFar);
7037 } else {
7038 // Jump to the false block if true.
7039 __ JumpIfNotHoleNan(input, scratch, if_false()->label(), Label::kFar);
7040 // Jump to the true block if it's not the next block.
7041 if (!fallthrough_when_true) {
7042 __ Jump(if_true()->label(), Label::kFar);
7043 }
7044 }
7045}

7047void HoleyFloat64IsHole::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
7048 UseRegister(input());
7049 DefineAsRegister(this);
7050 set_temporaries_needed(1);
7051}
7052void HoleyFloat64IsHole::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
7053 const ProcessingState& state) {
7054 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
7055 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7056 DoubleRegister value = ToDoubleRegister(input());
7057 Label done, if_not_hole;
7058 __ JumpIfNotHoleNan(value, scratch, &if_not_hole, Label::kNear);
7059 __ LoadRoot(ToRegister(result()), RootIndex::kTrueValue);
7060 __ Jump(&done);
7061 __ bind(&if_not_hole);
7062 __ LoadRoot(ToRegister(result()), RootIndex::kFalseValue);
7063 __ bind(&done);
7064}

7118void BranchIfUndefinedOrNull::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
7119 const ProcessingState& state) {
7120 Register value = ToRegister(condition_input());
7121 __ JumpIfRoot(value, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue, if_true()->label());
7122 __ JumpIfRoot(value, RootIndex::kNullValue, if_true()->label());
7123 auto* next_block = state.next_block();
7124 if (if_false() != next_block) {
7125 __ Jump(if_false()->label());
7126 }

7129void BranchIfUndetectable::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
7130 UseRegister(condition_input());
7131 set_temporaries_needed(1);
7132}
7133void BranchIfUndetectable::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
7134 const ProcessingState& state) {
7135 Register value = ToRegister(condition_input());
7136 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
7137 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7138
7139 auto* next_block = state.next_block();
7140 if (next_block == if_true() || next_block != if_false()) {
7141 __ JumpIfNotUndetectable(value, scratch, check_type(), if_false()->label());
7142 if (next_block != if_true()) {
7143 __ Jump(if_true()->label());
7144 }
7145 } else {
7146 __ JumpIfUndetectable(value, scratch, check_type(), if_true()->label());
7147 }
7148}
