7150void TestUndetectable::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
7151 UseRegister(value());
7152 set_temporaries_needed(1);
7153 DefineAsRegister(this);
7154}
7155void TestUndetectable::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
7156 const ProcessingState& state) {
7157 Register object = ToRegister(value());
7158 Register return_value = ToRegister(result());
7159 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
7160 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7161
7162 Label return_false, done;
7163 __ JumpIfNotUndetectable(object, scratch, check_type(), &return_false,
7164 Label::kNear);
7165
7166 __ LoadRoot(return_value, RootIndex::kTrueValue);
7167 __ Jump(&done, Label::kNear);
7168
7169 __ bind(&return_false);
7170 __ LoadRoot(return_value, RootIndex::kFalseValue);
7171
7172 __ bind(&done);
7173}

7199void Switch::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
7200 UseAndClobberRegister(value());
7201 set_temporaries_needed(1);
7202}
7203void Switch::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm, const ProcessingState& state) {
7204 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
7205 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7206 std::unique_ptr<Label*[]> labels = std::make_unique<Label*[]>(size());
7207 for (int i = 0; i < size(); i++) {
7208 BasicBlock* block = (targets())[i].block_ptr();
7209 block->set_start_block_of_switch_case(true);
7210 labels[i] = block->label();
7211 }
7212 Register val = ToRegister(value());
7213 // Switch requires {val} (the switch's condition) to be 64-bit, but maglev
7214 // usually manipulates/creates 32-bit integers. We thus sign-extend {val} to
7215 // 64-bit to have the correct value for negative numbers.
7216 __ SignExtend32To64Bits(val, val);
7217 __ Switch(scratch, val, value_base(), labels.get(), size());
7218 if (has_fallthrough()) {
7219 // If we jump-thread the fallthrough, it's not necessarily the next block.
7220 if (fallthrough() != state.next_block()) {
7221 __ Jump(fallthrough()->label());
7222 }
7223 } else {
7224 __ Trap();
7225 }
7226}
7227
7228void HandleNoHeapWritesInterrupt::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
7229 const ProcessingState& state) {
7230 ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
7231 Label* deferred = __ MakeDeferredCode(
7232 [](MaglevAssembler* masm, ZoneLabelRef done, Node* node) {
7233 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm, "HandleNoHeapWritesInterrupt");
7234 {
7235 SaveRegisterStateForCall save_register_state(
7236 masm, node->register_snapshot());
7237 __ Move(kContextRegister, masm->native_context().object());
7238 __ CallRuntime(Runtime::kHandleNoHeapWritesInterrupts, 0);
7239 save_register_state.DefineSafepointWithLazyDeopt(
7240 node->lazy_deopt_info());
7241 }
7242 __ Jump(*done);
7243 },
7244 done, this);
7245
7246 MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
7247 Register scratch = temps.AcquireScratch();
7248 MemOperand check = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
7249 ExternalReference::address_of_no_heap_write_interrupt_request(
7250 masm->isolate()),
7251 scratch);
7252 __ CompareByteAndJumpIf(check, 0, kNotEqual, scratch, deferred, Label::kFar);
7253 __ bind(*done);
7254}

7852// Keeping track of the effects this instruction has on known node aspects.
7853void NodeBase::ClearElementsProperties(KnownNodeAspects& known_node_aspects) {
7854 DCHECK(IsElementsArrayWrite(opcode()));
7855 // Clear Elements cache.
7856 auto elements_properties = known_node_aspects.loaded_properties.find(
7857 KnownNodeAspects::LoadedPropertyMapKey::Elements());
7858 if (elements_properties != known_node_aspects.loaded_properties.end()) {
7859 elements_properties->second.clear();
7860 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
7861 std::cout << " * Removing non-constant cached [Elements]";
7862 }
7863 }
7864}
7865
7866void NodeBase::ClearUnstableNodeAspects(KnownNodeAspects& known_node_aspects) {
7867 DCHECK(properties().can_write());
7868 DCHECK(!IsSimpleFieldStore(opcode()));
7869 DCHECK(!IsElementsArrayWrite(opcode()));
7870 known_node_aspects.ClearUnstableNodeAspects();
7871}
7872
7873void StoreMap::ClearUnstableNodeAspects(KnownNodeAspects& known_node_aspects) {
7874 switch (kind()) {
7875 case Kind::kInitializing:
7876 case Kind::kInitializingYoung:
7877 return;
7878 case Kind::kTransitioning: {
7879 if (NodeInfo* node_info =
7880 known_node_aspects.TryGetInfoFor(object_input().node())) {
7881 if (node_info->possible_maps_are_known() &&
7882 node_info->possible_maps().size() == 1) {
7883 compiler::MapRef old_map = node_info->possible_maps().at(0);
7884 auto MaybeAliases = [&](compiler::MapRef map) -> bool {
7885 return map.equals(old_map);
7886 };
7887 known_node_aspects.ClearUnstableMapsIfAny(MaybeAliases);
7888 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
7889 std::cout << " ! StoreMap: Clearing unstable map "
7890 << Brief(*old_map.object()) << std::endl;
7891 }
7892 return;
7893 }
7894 }
7895 break;
7896 }
7897 }
7898 // TODO(olivf): Only invalidate nodes with the same type.
7899 known_node_aspects.ClearUnstableMaps();
7900 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
7901 std::cout << " ! StoreMap: Clearing unstable maps" << std::endl;
7902 }
7903}
